{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884786777,"sessionID":"ses_28506bbdeffedjQVhzWWbAvMbe","part":{"id":"prt_d7afa729c0018S6Fyc8KXtALtX","messageID":"msg_d7afa58db001yXu6SFJ4V5Lk7l","sessionID":"ses_28506bbdeffedjQVhzWWbAvMbe","type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"toolu_69afb76ef01d4604848a18f1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md","newString":"# Delta Spec: AR-041 — E2E 集成测试\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing E2E integration tests for the agentcube client-go library.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-041\n- **Module**: `test/e2e`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: L\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe client-go library provides Kubernetes client code for the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group. It includes:\n- Clientset with typed clients for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n- SharedInformerFactory for caching resources\n- Listers for efficient resource access\n- Fake clients for testing purposes\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Feature: Clientset 创建与配置\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-001-A — 创建标准 Clientset\n\n- **GIVEN** 有效的 Kubernetes rest.Config 配置\n- **WHEN** 调用 `NewForConfig(config)` 创建 Clientset\n- **THEN** 返回非 nil 的 Clientset 实例\n- **AND** 可以通过 `RuntimeV1alpha1()` 访问 v1alpha1 API\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-001-B — 使用 httpClient 创建 Clientset\n\n- **GIVEN** 有效的 Kubernetes rest.Config 和自定义 http.Client\n- **WHEN** 调用 `NewForConfigAndClient(config, httpClient)` 创建 Clientset\n- **THEN** 返回的 Clientset 使用自定义的 httpClient\n- **AND** 所有 API 请求通过自定义的 httpClient 发起\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-001-C — 使用 NewForConfigOrDie 创建 Clientset\n\n- **GIVEN** 有效的 Kubernetes rest.Config 配置\n- **WHEN** 调用 `NewForConfigOrDie(config)` 创建 Clientset\n- **AND** 配置无效时 panic，否则返回正常的 Clientset\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-001-D — 使用 REST 接口创建 Clientset\n\n- **GIVEN** 一个 rest.Interface 实例\n- **WHEN** 调用 `New(restClient)` 创建 Clientset\n- **THEN** 返回的 Clientset 使用传入的 REST 客户端\n- **AND** 支持 RuntimeV1alpha1() 访问\n\n---\n\n### Feature: AgentRuntime CRUD 操作\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-002-A — 创建 AgentRuntime 资源\n\n- **GIVEN** 有效的 AgentRuntime 对象和命名空间 \"default\"\n- **WHEN** 调用 `clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Create(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.CreateOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回创建的 AgentRuntime 对象\n- **AND** 其 Name 与输入对象一致\n- **AND** 其 Namespace 为 \"default\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-002-B — 获取 AgentRuntime 资源\n\n- **GIVEN** 已存在的 AgentRuntime 资源 \"test-runtime\" 在命名空间 \"default\" 中\n- **WHEN** 调用 `clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Get(ctx, \"test-runtime\", metav1.GetOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回对应的 AgentRuntime 对象\n- **AND** 其 Name 为 \"test-runtime\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-002-C — 更新 AgentRuntime 资源\n\n- **GIVEN** 已存在的 AgentRuntime 资源 \"test-runtime\"\n- **WHEN** 调用 `Update(ctx, updatedAgentRuntime, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回更新后的 AgentRuntime 对象\n- **AND** 更新内容已持久化\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-002-D — 更新 AgentRuntime 状态\n\n- **GIVEN** 已存在的 AgentRuntime 资源\n- **WHEN** 调用 `UpdateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回状态已更新的 AgentRuntime 对象\n- **AND** Status 字段已修改\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-002-E — 删除 AgentRuntime 资源\n\n- **GIVEN** 已存在的 AgentRuntime 资源 \"test-runtime\"\n- **WHEN** 调用 `Delete(ctx, \"test-runtime\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回 nil 错误\n- **AND** 资源已被删除\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-002-F — 批量删除 AgentRuntime 资源\n\n- **GIVEN** 多个 AgentRuntime 资源在命名空间中\n- **WHEN** 调用 `DeleteCollection(ctx, deleteOptions, listOptions)`\n- **THEN** 返回 nil 错误\n- **AND** 所有匹配的资源已被删除\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-002-G — 列出所有 AgentRuntime 资源\n\n- **GIVEN** 多个 AgentRuntime 资源存在于集群中\n- **WHEN** 调用 `List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回 AgentRuntimeList 包含所有资源\n- **AND** Items 数组包含所有 AgentRuntime 对象\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-002-H — Watch AgentRuntime 资源变化\n\n- **GIVEN** 有效的 ListOptions 配置\n- **WHEN** 调用 `Watch(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回 watch.Interface\n- **AND** 可以接收资源变更事件\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-002-I — Patch AgentRuntime 资源\n\n- **GIVEN** 已存在的 AgentRuntime 资源和 patch 数据\n- **WHEN** 调用 `Patch(ctx, \"test-runtime\", patchType, data, metav1.PatchOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回 patch 后的 AgentRuntime 对象\n\n---\n\n### Feature: CodeInterpreter CRUD 操作\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-003-A — 创建 CodeInterpreter 资源\n\n- **GIVEN** 有效的 CodeInterpreter 对象和命名空间 \"default\"\n- **WHEN** 调用 `clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(\"default\").Create(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.CreateOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回创建的 CodeInterpreter 对象\n- **AND** 其 Name 与输入对象一致\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-003-B — 获取 CodeInterpreter 资源\n\n- **GIVEN** 已存在的 CodeInterpreter 资源 \"test-interpreter\"\n- **WHEN** 调用 `clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(\"default\").Get(ctx, \"test-interpreter\", metav1.GetOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回对应的 CodeInterpreter 对象\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-003-C — 更新 CodeInterpreter 资源\n\n- **GIVEN** 已存在的 CodeInterpreter 资源\n- **WHEN** 调用 `Update(ctx, updatedCodeInterpreter, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回更新后的 CodeInterpreter 对象\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-003-D — 删除 CodeInterpreter 资源\n\n- **GIVEN** 已存在的 CodeInterpreter 资源\n- **WHEN** 调用 `Delete(ctx, \"test-interpreter\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回 nil 错误\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-003-E — 列出所有 CodeInterpreter 资源\n\n- **GIVEN** 多个 CodeInterpreter 资源存在\n- **WHEN** 调用 `List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回 CodeInterpreterList 包含所有资源\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Informer Factory 使用\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-004-A — 创建 SharedInformerFactory\n\n- **GIVEN** 一个有效的 versioned.Clientset\n- **WHEN** 调用 `NewSharedInformerFactory(clientset, 30*time.Second)`\n- **THEN** 返回 SharedInformerFactory 实例\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-004-B — 启动 Informer\n\n- **GIVEN** 已创建的 SharedInformerFactory\n- **WHEN** 调用 `factory.Start(stopCh)`\n- **THEN** 所有已注册的 informer 开始同步\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-004-C — 等待缓存同步\n\n- **GIVEN** 正在运行的 Informer Factory\n- **WHEN** 调用 `factory.WaitForCacheSync(stopCh)`\n- **THEN** 返回 map[reflect.Type]bool 表示各资源类型的同步状态\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-004-D — 获取 AgentRuntime Informer\n\n- **GIVEN** 已启动的 SharedInformerFactory\n- **WHEN** 调用 `factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes()`\n- **THEN** 返回 AgentRuntimeInformer\n- **AND** 可以获取 Informer 和 Lister\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-004-E — 获取 CodeInterpreter Informer\n\n- **GIVEN** 已启动的 SharedInformerFactory\n- **WHEN** 调用 `factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters()`\n- **THEN** 返回 CodeInterpreterInformer\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-004-F — 使用自定义 resync 间隔\n\n- **GIVEN** versioned.Clientset\n- **WHEN** 调用 `NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client, 60*time.Second, WithCustomResyncConfig(...))`\n- **THEN** Informer 使用自定义的 resync 间隔\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-004-G — 使用 namespace 过滤\n\n- **GIVEN** 需要只监听特定命名空间\n- **WHEN** 使用 `WithNamespace(\"default\")` 选项\n- **THEN** Informer 只监听指定命名空间的资源\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-004-H — 使用 TweakListOptions 自定义 list 请求\n\n- **GIVEN** 需要自定义 list 查询参数\n- **WHEN** 使用 `WithTweakListOptions(func(*metav1.ListOptions))` 选项\n- **THEN** list 请求使用自定义的 ListOptions\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Lister 使用\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-005-A — 列出所有 AgentRuntime\n\n- **GIVEN** 已同步的 AgentRuntime Informer\n- **WHEN** 调用 `lister.List(labels.Everything())`\n- **THEN** 返回所有缓存的 AgentRuntime 对象\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-005-B — 按标签选择 AgentRuntime\n\n- **GIVEN** 已同步的 AgentRuntime 缓存\n- **WHEN** 调用 `lister.List(labels.SelectorFromSet(labels.Set{\"app\": \"test\"}))`\n- **THEN** 返回匹配标签的 AgentRuntime 对象\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-005-C — 获取指定命名空间的 AgentRuntime\n\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeLister 实例\n- **WHEN** 调用 `lister.AgentRuntimes(\"default\")`\n- **THEN** 返回 AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-005-D — 获取指定命名空间中的特定 AgentRuntime\n\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n- **WHEN** 调用 `nsLister.Get(\"test-runtime\")`\n- **THEN** 返回名称为 \"test-runtime\" 的 AgentRuntime 对象\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-005-E — CodeInterpreter Lister 使用\n\n- **GIVEN** 已同步的 CodeInterpreter 缓存\n- **WHEN** 调用 `lister.List(labels.Everything())`\n- **THEN** 返回所有缓存的 CodeInterpreter 对象\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Fake Client 使用\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-006-A — 创建 Fake Clientset\n\n- **GIVEN** 无需连接真实集群\n- **WHEN** 调用 `fake.NewSimpleClientset(...)`\n- **THEN** 返回内存中的 fake Clientset\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-006-B — Fake Client 执行 Create 操作\n\n- **GIVEN** Fake Clientset\n- **WHEN** 调用 `fakeClientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Create(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.CreateOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回创建的对象存储在内存中\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-006-C — Fake Client 执行 Get 操作\n\n- **GIVEN** 已通过 Create 存入的 AgentRuntime\n- **WHEN** 通过 fake Clientset 获取\n- **THEN** 返回之前存储的对象\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-006-D — Fake Client 执行 List 操作\n\n- **GIVEN** 多个已存储的 AgentRuntime\n- **WHEN** 通过 fake Clientset 列出\n- **THEN** 返回所有已存储的对象\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-006-E — Fake Client 执行 Watch 操作\n\n- **GIVEN** Fake Clientset 和 watch 客户端\n- **WHEN** 调用 `Watch(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回可以接收事件的 watch.Interface\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-006-F — Fake Scheme 注册\n\n- **GIVEN** Fake Clientset\n- **WHEN** 执行资源操作\n- **THEN** 自动使用注册的 Scheme 进行序列化\n\n---\n\n### Feature: 完整 E2E 流程测试\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-007-A — 完整的 AgentRuntime 生命周期\n\n- **GIVEN** 运行的 Kubernetes 集群和有效配置\n- **WHEN** 按顺序执行: Create → Get → Update → UpdateStatus → Delete\n- **THEN** 完整生命周期正确执行\n- **AND** 每步操作返回正确的对象和状态\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-007-B — 使用 Informer 和 Lister 进行资源监听\n\n- **GIVEN** 运行的集群和 Clientset\n- **WHEN** 创建 SharedInformerFactory → 启动 → 等待同步 → 使用 Lister 查询\n- **THEN** Lister 返回的缓存数据与直接 API 查询一致\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-007-C — 并发资源操作\n\n- **GIVEN** 多个并发创建的请求\n- **WHEN** 同时创建多个 AgentRuntime 资源\n- **THEN** 所有资源正确创建\n- **AND** 最终列表包含所有资源\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-007-D — 错误处理 - 资源不存在\n\n- **GIVEN** 不存在的资源名称\n- **WHEN** 调用 Get 操作\n- **THEN** 返回 `errors.IsNotFound(err)` 为 true\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-007-E — 错误处理 - 权限不足\n\n- **GIVEN** 没有创建权限的配置\n- **WHEN** 尝试创建资源\n- **THEN** 返回包含 \"forbidden\" 或类似信息的错误\n\n---\n\n### Feature: 集成场景测试\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-008-A — AgentRuntime 与 CodeInterpreter 关联\n\n- **GIVEN** 需要创建关联的资源\n- **WHEN** 先创建 AgentRuntime，再创建引用它的 CodeInterpreter\n- **THEN** CodeInterpreter 能正确引用 AgentRuntime\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-008-B — 批量操作性能测试\n\n- **GIVEN** 大批量资源\n- **WHEN** 创建 1000 个 AgentRuntime 资源\n- **THEN** 所有资源创建成功\n- **AND** List 操作在合理时间内返回\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-008-C — Informer 事件处理\n\n- **GIVEN** 运行中的 Informer 和资源变化\n- **WHEN** 外部创建/更新/删除资源\n- **THEN** Informer 事件被正确触发\n- **AND** Lister 缓存同步更新\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC001: Clientset 创建测试通过 (NewForConfig, NewForConfigAndClient, NewForConfigOrDie, New)\n- [ ] AC002: AgentRuntime CRUD 操作测试通过 (Create, Get, Update, UpdateStatus, Delete, DeleteCollection, List, Watch, Patch)\n- [ ] AC003: CodeInterpreter CRUD 操作测试通过\n- [ ] AC004: SharedInformerFactory 测试通过 (创建, 启动, 等待同步, 获取 informer)\n- [ ] AC005: AgentRuntime 和 CodeInterpreter Informer 测试通过\n- [ ] AC006: Informer Factory 选项测试通过 (WithCustomResyncConfig, WithNamespace, WithTweakListOptions)\n- [ ] AC007: Lister 测试通过 (List, Get, namespace lister)\n- [ ] AC008: Fake Client 测试通过 (Create, Get, List, Watch)\n- [ ] AC009: 完整生命周期测试通过\n- [ ] AC010: 错误处理测试通过 (NotFound, Forbidden)\n\n---\n\n## Test File Status\n\n| Source File | Test File | Status |\n|-------------|-----------|--------|\n| clientset.go | clientset_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n| runtime_client.go | runtime_client_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n| agentruntime.go | agentruntime_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n| codeinterpreter.go | codeinterpreter_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n| factory.go | factory_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n| agentruntime.go (informer) | agentruntime_informer_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n| codeinterpreter.go (informer) | codeinterpreter_informer_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n| agentruntime.go (lister) | agentruntime_lister_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n| codeinterpreter.go (lister) | codeinterpreter_lister_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n| fake/clientset.go | fake_clientset_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n\n---\n\n## Testing Patterns\n\n### Test Environment Setup\n- Use envtest (kubebuilder) for integration tests\n- Create temporary Kubernetes API server for testing\n- Use fake clients for unit tests\n\n### E2E Test Structure\n```go\nfunc TestAgentRuntimeE2E(t *testing.T) {\n    // Setup: Start test environment\n    // Given: Create test resources\n    // When: Perform operations\n    // Then: Verify results\n}\n```\n\n### Test File Naming\n- Follow Go convention: `*_test.go`\n- E2E tests in `test/e2e/` package\n- Use `testify` for assertions\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Client-go library: `client-go/`\n- API Group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh / v1alpha1`\n- Resources: AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter\n- Source reference: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`","oldString":"- Client-go library: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n- API Group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh / v1alpha1`\n- Resources: AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md\n===================================================================\n--- /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md\n+++ /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md\n@@ -1314,7 +1314,413 @@\n ---\n \n ## References\n \n-- Client-go library: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n+# Delta Spec: AR-041 — E2E 集成测试\n+\n+## Overview\n+\n+This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing E2E integration tests for the agentcube client-go library.\n+\n+## Base Specifications\n+\n+- **AR**: AR-041\n+- **Module**: `test/e2e`\n+- **Language**: Go\n+- **Size**: L\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Background\n+\n+The client-go library provides Kubernetes client code for the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group. It includes:\n+- Clientset with typed clients for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n+- SharedInformerFactory for caching resources\n+- Listers for efficient resource access\n+- Fake clients for testing purposes\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirements\n+\n+### Feature: Clientset 创建与配置\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-001-A — 创建标准 Clientset\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 有效的 Kubernetes rest.Config 配置\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `NewForConfig(config)` 创建 Clientset\n+- **THEN** 返回非 nil 的 Clientset 实例\n+- **AND** 可以通过 `RuntimeV1alpha1()` 访问 v1alpha1 API\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-001-B — 使用 httpClient 创建 Clientset\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 有效的 Kubernetes rest.Config 和自定义 http.Client\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `NewForConfigAndClient(config, httpClient)` 创建 Clientset\n+- **THEN** 返回的 Clientset 使用自定义的 httpClient\n+- **AND** 所有 API 请求通过自定义的 httpClient 发起\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-001-C — 使用 NewForConfigOrDie 创建 Clientset\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 有效的 Kubernetes rest.Config 配置\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `NewForConfigOrDie(config)` 创建 Clientset\n+- **AND** 配置无效时 panic，否则返回正常的 Clientset\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-001-D — 使用 REST 接口创建 Clientset\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 一个 rest.Interface 实例\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `New(restClient)` 创建 Clientset\n+- **THEN** 返回的 Clientset 使用传入的 REST 客户端\n+- **AND** 支持 RuntimeV1alpha1() 访问\n+\n+---\n+\n+### Feature: AgentRuntime CRUD 操作\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-002-A — 创建 AgentRuntime 资源\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 有效的 AgentRuntime 对象和命名空间 \"default\"\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Create(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.CreateOptions{})`\n+- **THEN** 返回创建的 AgentRuntime 对象\n+- **AND** 其 Name 与输入对象一致\n+- **AND** 其 Namespace 为 \"default\"\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-002-B — 获取 AgentRuntime 资源\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 已存在的 AgentRuntime 资源 \"test-runtime\" 在命名空间 \"default\" 中\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Get(ctx, \"test-runtime\", metav1.GetOptions{})`\n+- **THEN** 返回对应的 AgentRuntime 对象\n+- **AND** 其 Name 为 \"test-runtime\"\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-002-C — 更新 AgentRuntime 资源\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 已存在的 AgentRuntime 资源 \"test-runtime\"\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `Update(ctx, updatedAgentRuntime, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`\n+- **THEN** 返回更新后的 AgentRuntime 对象\n+- **AND** 更新内容已持久化\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-002-D — 更新 AgentRuntime 状态\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 已存在的 AgentRuntime 资源\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `UpdateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`\n+- **THEN** 返回状态已更新的 AgentRuntime 对象\n+- **AND** Status 字段已修改\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-002-E — 删除 AgentRuntime 资源\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 已存在的 AgentRuntime 资源 \"test-runtime\"\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `Delete(ctx, \"test-runtime\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})`\n+- **THEN** 返回 nil 错误\n+- **AND** 资源已被删除\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-002-F — 批量删除 AgentRuntime 资源\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 多个 AgentRuntime 资源在命名空间中\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `DeleteCollection(ctx, deleteOptions, listOptions)`\n+- **THEN** 返回 nil 错误\n+- **AND** 所有匹配的资源已被删除\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-002-G — 列出所有 AgentRuntime 资源\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 多个 AgentRuntime 资源存在于集群中\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`\n+- **THEN** 返回 AgentRuntimeList 包含所有资源\n+- **AND** Items 数组包含所有 AgentRuntime 对象\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-002-H — Watch AgentRuntime 资源变化\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 有效的 ListOptions 配置\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `Watch(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`\n+- **THEN** 返回 watch.Interface\n+- **AND** 可以接收资源变更事件\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-002-I — Patch AgentRuntime 资源\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 已存在的 AgentRuntime 资源和 patch 数据\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `Patch(ctx, \"test-runtime\", patchType, data, metav1.PatchOptions{})`\n+- **THEN** 返回 patch 后的 AgentRuntime 对象\n+\n+---\n+\n+### Feature: CodeInterpreter CRUD 操作\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-003-A — 创建 CodeInterpreter 资源\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 有效的 CodeInterpreter 对象和命名空间 \"default\"\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(\"default\").Create(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.CreateOptions{})`\n+- **THEN** 返回创建的 CodeInterpreter 对象\n+- **AND** 其 Name 与输入对象一致\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-003-B — 获取 CodeInterpreter 资源\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 已存在的 CodeInterpreter 资源 \"test-interpreter\"\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(\"default\").Get(ctx, \"test-interpreter\", metav1.GetOptions{})`\n+- **THEN** 返回对应的 CodeInterpreter 对象\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-003-C — 更新 CodeInterpreter 资源\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 已存在的 CodeInterpreter 资源\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `Update(ctx, updatedCodeInterpreter, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`\n+- **THEN** 返回更新后的 CodeInterpreter 对象\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-003-D — 删除 CodeInterpreter 资源\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 已存在的 CodeInterpreter 资源\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `Delete(ctx, \"test-interpreter\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})`\n+- **THEN** 返回 nil 错误\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-003-E — 列出所有 CodeInterpreter 资源\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 多个 CodeInterpreter 资源存在\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`\n+- **THEN** 返回 CodeInterpreterList 包含所有资源\n+\n+---\n+\n+### Feature: Informer Factory 使用\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-004-A — 创建 SharedInformerFactory\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 一个有效的 versioned.Clientset\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `NewSharedInformerFactory(clientset, 30*time.Second)`\n+- **THEN** 返回 SharedInformerFactory 实例\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-004-B — 启动 Informer\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 已创建的 SharedInformerFactory\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `factory.Start(stopCh)`\n+- **THEN** 所有已注册的 informer 开始同步\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-004-C — 等待缓存同步\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 正在运行的 Informer Factory\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `factory.WaitForCacheSync(stopCh)`\n+- **THEN** 返回 map[reflect.Type]bool 表示各资源类型的同步状态\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-004-D — 获取 AgentRuntime Informer\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 已启动的 SharedInformerFactory\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes()`\n+- **THEN** 返回 AgentRuntimeInformer\n+- **AND** 可以获取 Informer 和 Lister\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-004-E — 获取 CodeInterpreter Informer\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 已启动的 SharedInformerFactory\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters()`\n+- **THEN** 返回 CodeInterpreterInformer\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-004-F — 使用自定义 resync 间隔\n+\n+- **GIVEN** versioned.Clientset\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client, 60*time.Second, WithCustomResyncConfig(...))`\n+- **THEN** Informer 使用自定义的 resync 间隔\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-004-G — 使用 namespace 过滤\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 需要只监听特定命名空间\n+- **WHEN** 使用 `WithNamespace(\"default\")` 选项\n+- **THEN** Informer 只监听指定命名空间的资源\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-004-H — 使用 TweakListOptions 自定义 list 请求\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 需要自定义 list 查询参数\n+- **WHEN** 使用 `WithTweakListOptions(func(*metav1.ListOptions))` 选项\n+- **THEN** list 请求使用自定义的 ListOptions\n+\n+---\n+\n+### Feature: Lister 使用\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-005-A — 列出所有 AgentRuntime\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 已同步的 AgentRuntime Informer\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `lister.List(labels.Everything())`\n+- **THEN** 返回所有缓存的 AgentRuntime 对象\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-005-B — 按标签选择 AgentRuntime\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 已同步的 AgentRuntime 缓存\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `lister.List(labels.SelectorFromSet(labels.Set{\"app\": \"test\"}))`\n+- **THEN** 返回匹配标签的 AgentRuntime 对象\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-005-C — 获取指定命名空间的 AgentRuntime\n+\n+- **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeLister 实例\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `lister.AgentRuntimes(\"default\")`\n+- **THEN** 返回 AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-005-D — 获取指定命名空间中的特定 AgentRuntime\n+\n+- **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `nsLister.Get(\"test-runtime\")`\n+- **THEN** 返回名称为 \"test-runtime\" 的 AgentRuntime 对象\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-005-E — CodeInterpreter Lister 使用\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 已同步的 CodeInterpreter 缓存\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `lister.List(labels.Everything())`\n+- **THEN** 返回所有缓存的 CodeInterpreter 对象\n+\n+---\n+\n+### Feature: Fake Client 使用\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-006-A — 创建 Fake Clientset\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 无需连接真实集群\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `fake.NewSimpleClientset(...)`\n+- **THEN** 返回内存中的 fake Clientset\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-006-B — Fake Client 执行 Create 操作\n+\n+- **GIVEN** Fake Clientset\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `fakeClientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Create(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.CreateOptions{})`\n+- **THEN** 返回创建的对象存储在内存中\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-006-C — Fake Client 执行 Get 操作\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 已通过 Create 存入的 AgentRuntime\n+- **WHEN** 通过 fake Clientset 获取\n+- **THEN** 返回之前存储的对象\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-006-D — Fake Client 执行 List 操作\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 多个已存储的 AgentRuntime\n+- **WHEN** 通过 fake Clientset 列出\n+- **THEN** 返回所有已存储的对象\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-006-E — Fake Client 执行 Watch 操作\n+\n+- **GIVEN** Fake Clientset 和 watch 客户端\n+- **WHEN** 调用 `Watch(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`\n+- **THEN** 返回可以接收事件的 watch.Interface\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-006-F — Fake Scheme 注册\n+\n+- **GIVEN** Fake Clientset\n+- **WHEN** 执行资源操作\n+- **THEN** 自动使用注册的 Scheme 进行序列化\n+\n+---\n+\n+### Feature: 完整 E2E 流程测试\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-007-A — 完整的 AgentRuntime 生命周期\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 运行的 Kubernetes 集群和有效配置\n+- **WHEN** 按顺序执行: Create → Get → Update → UpdateStatus → Delete\n+- **THEN** 完整生命周期正确执行\n+- **AND** 每步操作返回正确的对象和状态\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-007-B — 使用 Informer 和 Lister 进行资源监听\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 运行的集群和 Clientset\n+- **WHEN** 创建 SharedInformerFactory → 启动 → 等待同步 → 使用 Lister 查询\n+- **THEN** Lister 返回的缓存数据与直接 API 查询一致\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-007-C — 并发资源操作\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 多个并发创建的请求\n+- **WHEN** 同时创建多个 AgentRuntime 资源\n+- **THEN** 所有资源正确创建\n+- **AND** 最终列表包含所有资源\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-007-D — 错误处理 - 资源不存在\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 不存在的资源名称\n+- **WHEN** 调用 Get 操作\n+- **THEN** 返回 `errors.IsNotFound(err)` 为 true\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-007-E — 错误处理 - 权限不足\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 没有创建权限的配置\n+- **WHEN** 尝试创建资源\n+- **THEN** 返回包含 \"forbidden\" 或类似信息的错误\n+\n+---\n+\n+### Feature: 集成场景测试\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-008-A — AgentRuntime 与 CodeInterpreter 关联\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 需要创建关联的资源\n+- **WHEN** 先创建 AgentRuntime，再创建引用它的 CodeInterpreter\n+- **THEN** CodeInterpreter 能正确引用 AgentRuntime\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-008-B — 批量操作性能测试\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 大批量资源\n+- **WHEN** 创建 1000 个 AgentRuntime 资源\n+- **THEN** 所有资源创建成功\n+- **AND** List 操作在合理时间内返回\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-041-008-C — Informer 事件处理\n+\n+- **GIVEN** 运行中的 Informer 和资源变化\n+- **WHEN** 外部创建/更新/删除资源\n+- **THEN** Informer 事件被正确触发\n+- **AND** Lister 缓存同步更新\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Acceptance Criteria\n+\n+- [ ] AC001: Clientset 创建测试通过 (NewForConfig, NewForConfigAndClient, NewForConfigOrDie, New)\n+- [ ] AC002: AgentRuntime CRUD 操作测试通过 (Create, Get, Update, UpdateStatus, Delete, DeleteCollection, List, Watch, Patch)\n+- [ ] AC003: CodeInterpreter CRUD 操作测试通过\n+- [ ] AC004: SharedInformerFactory 测试通过 (创建, 启动, 等待同步, 获取 informer)\n+- [ ] AC005: AgentRuntime 和 CodeInterpreter Informer 测试通过\n+- [ ] AC006: Informer Factory 选项测试通过 (WithCustomResyncConfig, WithNamespace, WithTweakListOptions)\n+- [ ] AC007: Lister 测试通过 (List, Get, namespace lister)\n+- [ ] AC008: Fake Client 测试通过 (Create, Get, List, Watch)\n+- [ ] AC009: 完整生命周期测试通过\n+- [ ] AC010: 错误处理测试通过 (NotFound, Forbidden)\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Test File Status\n+\n+| Source File | Test File | Status |\n+|-------------|-----------|--------|\n+| clientset.go | clientset_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n+| runtime_client.go | runtime_client_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n+| agentruntime.go | agentruntime_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n+| codeinterpreter.go | codeinterpreter_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n+| factory.go | factory_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n+| agentruntime.go (informer) | agentruntime_informer_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n+| codeinterpreter.go (informer) | codeinterpreter_informer_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n+| agentruntime.go (lister) | agentruntime_lister_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n+| codeinterpreter.go (lister) | codeinterpreter_lister_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n+| fake/clientset.go | fake_clientset_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Testing Patterns\n+\n+### Test Environment Setup\n+- Use envtest (kubebuilder) for integration tests\n+- Create temporary Kubernetes API server for testing\n+- Use fake clients for unit tests\n+\n+### E2E Test Structure\n+```go\n+func TestAgentRuntimeE2E(t *testing.T) {\n+    // Setup: Start test environment\n+    // Given: Create test resources\n+    // When: Perform operations\n+    // Then: Verify results\n+}\n+```\n+\n+### Test File Naming\n+- Follow Go convention: `*_test.go`\n+- E2E tests in `test/e2e/` package\n+- Use `testify` for assertions\n+\n+---\n+\n+## References\n+\n+- Client-go library: `client-go/`\n - API Group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh / v1alpha1`\n-- Resources: AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter\n\\ No newline at end of file\n+- Resources: AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter\n+- Source reference: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n\\ No newline at end of file\n","filediff":{"file":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md","before":"# Delta Spec: AR-039 — Go Unit Testing (router/store/picod)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing Go unit tests for three core modules: router, store, and picod.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-039\n- **Module**: `pkg`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: L\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe agentcube project consists of three main modules requiring unit tests:\n\n1. **pkg/router**: HTTP routing, proxy, health checking, rate limiting, authentication, session management, JWT\n2. **pkg/store**: Valkey/Redis-backed session and sandbox storage\n3. **pkg/picod**: Pico execution server with command execution and file handling\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Feature: Router Module - Initialization and Configuration\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-001-A — Router creates with default config\n\n- **GIVEN** a nil config is passed to `NewRouter`\n- **WHEN** `NewRouter(config)` is called\n- **THEN** a Router instance is returned with default configuration values\n- **AND** default listen address is \":8080\"\n- **AND** backend timeout is 30 seconds\n- **AND** rate limiting is disabled by default\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-001-B — Router creates with custom config\n\n- **GIVEN** a Config with SessionEnabled=true and JWTEnabled=true\n- **WHEN** `NewRouter(config)` is called\n- **THEN** a Router instance is returned with SessionManager initialized\n- **AND** JWTManager is initialized\n- **AND** SessionHandler is registered for /v1/sessions\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-001-C — Router adds and removes backends\n\n- **GIVEN** a Router instance is created\n- **WHEN** `AddBackend(\"backend1\", \"http://localhost:8081\", \"/api\", \"backend-1\")` is called\n- **THEN** the backend is added to the pool\n- **WHEN** `RemoveBackend(\"backend1\")` is called\n- **THEN** the backend is removed from the pool\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Router Module - Backend Pool and Health Checking\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-002-A — Backend pool routes requests\n\n- **GIVEN** a BackendPool with multiple backends registered\n- **WHEN** `GetBackendForRequest()` is called with a path matching a backend prefix\n- **THEN** the matching backend is returned\n- **WHEN** `GetBackendForRequest()` is called with a non-matching path\n- **THEN** nil is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-002-B — Health checker monitors backends\n\n- **GIVEN** a BackendPool with registered backends\n- **WHEN** HealthChecker Start() is invoked\n- **THEN** periodic health checks run at configured interval\n- **WHEN** a backend becomes unhealthy\n- **THEN** the backend is marked as unavailable\n- **WHEN** HealthChecker Stop() is invoked\n- **THEN** health checking stops\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Router Module - Rate Limiting\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-003-A — Rate limiter allows requests under limit\n\n- **GIVEN** RateLimiter with RPS=10 and Burst=20\n- **WHEN** 5 requests arrive in quick succession\n- **THEN** all requests are allowed through\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-003-B — Rate limiter blocks requests over limit\n\n- **GIVEN** RateLimiter with RPS=2 and Burst=4\n- **WHEN** 10 requests arrive simultaneously\n- **THEN** requests beyond burst limit are blocked with 429 status\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-003-C — Rate limiter can be disabled\n\n- **GIVEN** RateLimiter with enabled=false\n- **WHEN** any number of requests arrive\n- **THEN** all requests pass through without rate limiting\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Router Module - Authentication\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-004-A — Authenticator validates token\n\n- **GIVEN** Authenticator with AuthEnabled=true and AuthToken=\"secret\"\n- **WHEN** request with \"Authorization: Bearer secret\" header arrives\n- **THEN** request is allowed\n- **WHEN** request with wrong token arrives\n- **THEN** request is rejected with 401 status\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-004-B — Authenticator can be disabled\n\n- **GIVEN** Authenticator with AuthEnabled=false\n- **WHEN** any request arrives\n- **THEN** request passes through without token validation\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Router Module - Session Management\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-005-A — Session manager creates session\n\n- **GIVEN** SessionManager with SessionEnabled=true\n- **WHEN** a new session is created via session store\n- **THEN** session ID is generated\n- **AND** session data is stored with expiry\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-005-B — Session manager cleanup removes expired sessions\n\n- **GIVEN** SessionManager with sessions in store\n- **WHEN** cleanup runs and finds expired sessions\n- **THEN** expired sessions are removed from store\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-005-C — Session middleware attaches session to request\n\n- **GIVEN** a request with valid session cookie\n- **WHEN** request passes through SessionMiddleware\n- **THEN** session info is available in request context\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Router Module - JWT Authentication\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-006-A — JWT manager creates token\n\n- **GIVEN** JWTManager configured with HS256 algorithm and secret=\"mysecret\"\n- **WHEN** `GenerateToken(claims)` is called with user claims\n- **THEN** a signed JWT token is returned\n- **AND** token contains correct issuer and audience\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-006-B — JWT manager validates token\n\n- **GIVEN** JWTManager configured with valid secret\n- **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called with a valid token\n- **THEN** claims are returned without error\n- **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called with an expired token\n- **THEN** error is returned indicating token expiration\n- **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called with invalid signature\n- **THEN** error is returned indicating invalid token\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-006-C — JWT middleware enforces authentication\n\n- **GIVEN** JWTMiddleware with JWTEnabled=true and JWTAllowQueryParam=false\n- **WHEN** request without JWT arrives at protected endpoint\n- **THEN** request is rejected with 401 status\n- **WHEN** request with valid JWT in Authorization header arrives\n- **THEN** request is allowed and claims available in context\n- **WHEN** JWTAllowQueryParam=true and JWT in query param\n- **THEN** request is allowed\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Router Module - Logging and Metrics\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-007-A — Logger records requests\n\n- **GIVEN** Logger middleware is in the chain\n- **WHEN** HTTP request arrives\n- **THEN** request details are logged including method, path, duration\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-007-B — Metrics records request stats\n\n- **GIVEN** Metrics instance\n- **WHEN** `IncBackendRequests(backend, status)` is called\n- **THEN** backend request counter increments\n- **WHEN** `RecordRequestDuration(method, path, backend, duration)` is called\n- **THEN** request duration is recorded\n- **WHEN** `IncErrors(errorType)` is called\n- **THEN** error counter increments\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Store Module - Store Interface\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-008-A — Store interface contract\n\n- **GIVEN** a Store implementation (Valkey or Redis)\n- **WHEN** all interface methods are called\n- **THEN** the Store implements the complete Store interface:\n  - Ping() error\n  - GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n  - StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error\n  - UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error\n  - DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) error\n  - ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n  - ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n  - UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at) error\n  - Close() error\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Store Module - Valkey Store\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-A — Valkey store connects with credentials\n\n- **GIVEN** environment variables VALKEY_ADDR and VALKEY_PASSWORD are set\n- **WHEN** `newValkeyStore()` is called\n- **THEN** a Valkey client connects successfully\n- **AND** ping returns \"PONG\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-B — Valkey store requires address\n\n- **GIVEN** VALKEY_ADDR is not set\n- **WHEN** `newValkeyStore()` is called\n- **THEN** error is returned indicating VALKEY_ADDR is required\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-C — Valkey store stores sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid SandboxInfo with SessionID and ExpiresAt\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** sandbox is stored in Valkey\n- **AND** session is added to expiry index\n- **AND** session is added to last activity index\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-D — Valkey store retrieves sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox was previously stored\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` is called\n- **THEN** correct SandboxInfo is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-E — Valkey store returns error for non-existent session\n\n- **GIVEN** a session ID that doesn't exist\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` is called\n- **THEN** ErrNotFound is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-F — Valkey store updates sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox exists in store\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** sandbox data is updated\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-G — Valkey store deletes sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox exists in store\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` is called\n- **THEN** sandbox is removed from store\n- **AND** session is removed from expiry index\n- **AND** session is removed from last activity index\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-H — Valkey store lists expired sandboxes\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple sandboxes with different expiry times\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** only sandboxes expiring before 'before' are returned\n- **AND** maximum of 'limit' results are returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-I — Valkey store lists inactive sandboxes\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple sandboxes with different last activity times\n- **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** only sandboxes inactive before 'before' are returned\n- **AND** maximum of 'limit' results are returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-J — Valkey store validates input\n\n- **GIVEN** nil sandbox passed to StoreSandbox\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n- **THEN** error \"sandbox is nil\" is returned\n\n- **GIVEN** sandbox with zero ExpiresAt\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** error \"invalid expiry: ExpiresAt is zero\" is returned\n\n- **GIVEN** sandbox with empty SessionID\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** error \"session ID is required\" is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-K — Valkey store updates last activity\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox exists in store\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, time)` is called\n- **THEN** last activity timestamp is updated in index\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-L — Valkey store closes connection\n\n- **GIVEN** a Valkey store is connected\n- **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n- **THEN** connection is closed\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Picod Module - Server Initialization\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-010-A — Server creates with valid config\n\n- **GIVEN** valid Config and AuthConfig\n- **WHEN** `NewServer(config, authConfig)` is called\n- **THEN** server instance is returned\n- **AND** Gin engine is configured\n- **AND** routes are registered\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-010-B — Server validates config\n\n- **GIVEN** Config with invalid values (e.g., negative port)\n- **WHEN** `NewServer(config, authConfig)` is called\n- **THEN** error is returned indicating invalid config\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-010-C — Server sets workspace directory\n\n- **GIVEN** Config with Workspace=\"/tmp/test-workspace\"\n- **WHEN** Server initializes\n- **THEN** workspace directory is created if not exists\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-010-D — Server creates with empty workspace\n\n- **GIVEN** Config with empty Workspace\n- **WHEN** Server initializes\n- **THEN** current working directory is used as workspace\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Picod Module - Path Sanitization\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-011-A — Path sanitization allows safe paths\n\n- **GIVEN** Server with workspace=\"/app\"\n- **WHEN** `sanitizePath(\"subdir/file.txt\")` is called\n- **THEN** resolved path within workspace is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-011-B — Path sanitization blocks escape attempts\n\n- **GIVEN** Server with workspace=\"/app\"\n- **WHEN** `sanitizePath(\"../../../etc/passwd\")` is called\n- **THEN** error \"access denied: path escapes workspace\" is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-011-C — Path sanitization blocks absolute paths\n\n- **GIVEN** Server with workspace=\"/app\"\n- **WHEN** `sanitizePath(\"/etc/passwd\")` is called\n- **THEN** error \"access denied: path escapes workspace\" is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-011-D — Path sanitization handles symlinks\n\n- **GIVEN** Server with workspace=\"/app\" and symlink /app/link -> /tmp\n- **WHEN** `sanitizePath(\"link/sensitive\")` is called\n- **THEN** error \"access denied: path escapes workspace\" is returned\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Picod Module - Authentication\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-012-A — Auth manager loads public key\n\n- **GIVEN** AuthConfig with valid RSA public key in PEM format\n- **WHEN** AuthManager initializes\n- **THEN** public key is loaded successfully\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-012-B — Auth manager validates JWT\n\n- **GIVEN** AuthManager with loaded public key\n- **WHEN** valid JWT token is validated\n- **THEN** claims are returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-012-C — Auth manager rejects invalid JWT\n\n- **GIVEN** AuthManager with loaded public key\n- **WHEN** invalid or expired JWT token is validated\n- **THEN** error is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-012-D — Auth middleware allows public paths\n\n- **GIVEN** request to public path like /health\n- **WHEN** request passes through auth middleware\n- **THEN** request is allowed without JWT validation\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-012-E — Auth middleware requires auth for protected paths\n\n- **GIVEN** request to protected path /api/execute without token\n- **WHEN** request passes through auth middleware\n- **THEN** request is rejected with 401\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Picod Module - Execute Handler\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-013-A — Execute handler runs valid command\n\n- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with Command=[\"echo\", \"hello\"]\n- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n- **THEN** response with stdout=\"hello\", ExitCode=0 is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-013-B — Execute handler fails on empty command\n\n- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with empty Command array\n- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n- **THEN** error response with code 400 is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-013-C — Execute handler respects timeout\n\n- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with Command=[\"sleep\", \"10\"] and Timeout=\"1s\"\n- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n- **THEN** response with ExitCode=124 (timeout) is returned\n- **AND** stderr indicates timeout\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-013-D — Execute handler validates working directory\n\n- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with WorkingDir=\"../../../etc\"\n- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n- **THEN** error response with code 400 is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-013-E — Execute handler captures stderr\n\n- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with Command=[\"ls\", \"/nonexistent\"]\n- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n- **THEN** response includes stderr output\n- **AND** non-zero ExitCode is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-013-F — Execute handler accepts custom environment\n\n- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with Command=[\"env\"] and Env={\"TEST_VAR\": \"test\"}\n- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n- **THEN** response stdout contains TEST_VAR=test\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Picod Module - File Handlers\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-014-A — Upload file handler saves file\n\n- **GIVEN** file upload request with valid content\n- **WHEN** UploadFileHandler processes request\n- **THEN** file is saved to workspace\n- **AND** success response is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-014-B — List files handler returns directory contents\n\n- **GIVEN** workspace with multiple files\n- **WHEN** ListFilesHandler is called\n- **THEN** list of files is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-014-C — Download file handler serves file\n\n- **GIVEN** file exists in workspace\n- **WHEN** DownloadFileHandler is called with path\n- **THEN** file content is served\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-014-D — Download file handler blocks path escape\n\n- **GIVEN** request for file outside workspace\n- **WHEN** DownloadFileHandler processes request\n- **THEN** request is rejected\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Picod Module - Health Check and RSA Key Loading\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-015-A — Health check returns healthy status\n\n- **GIVEN** Server is running\n- **WHEN** GET /health is requested\n- **THEN** response with status \"healthy\" is returned\n- **AND** HTTP 200 status code\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-015-B — LoadRSAPublicKey parses valid PEM\n\n- **GIVEN** valid RSA public key in PEM format\n- **WHEN** `LoadRSAPublicKey(pemData)` is called\n- **THEN** *rsa.PublicKey is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-015-C — LoadRSAPublicKey rejects invalid PEM\n\n- **GIVEN** invalid PEM data\n- **WHEN** `LoadRSAPublicKey(pemData)` is called\n- **THEN** error is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-015-D — LoadRSAPublicKey rejects non-RSA key\n\n- **GIVEN** PEM data containing non-RSA key\n- **WHEN** `LoadRSAPublicKey(pemData)` is called\n- **THEN** error \"public key is not an RSA key\" is returned\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n### Router Module\n- [ ] AC001: Unit tests for Config initialization and defaults\n- [ ] AC002: Unit tests for Router creation with various config combinations\n- [ ] AC003: Unit tests for BackendPool AddBackend, RemoveBackend, GetBackendForRequest\n- [ ] AC004: Unit tests for HealthChecker Start, Stop, checkBackend\n- [ ] AC005: Unit tests for RateLimiter Allow, Middleware\n- [ ] AC006: Unit tests for Authenticator Middleware with enabled/disabled states\n- [ ] AC007: Unit tests for SessionManager Create, Get, Delete, Cleanup\n- [ ] AC008: Unit tests for JWTManager GenerateToken, ValidateToken\n- [ ] AC009: Unit tests for JWTMiddleware with various configurations\n- [ ] AC010: Unit tests for Logger Middleware\n- [ ] AC011: Unit tests for Metrics IncBackendRequests, RecordRequestDuration, IncErrors\n\n### Store Module\n- [ ] AC012: Unit tests for Valkey store connection with mocked client\n- [ ] AC013: Unit tests for StoreSandbox with valid and invalid inputs\n- [ ] AC014: Unit tests for GetSandboxBySessionID with existing and non-existing sessions\n- [ ] AC015: Unit tests for UpdateSandbox\n- [ ] AC016: Unit tests for DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n- [ ] AC017: Unit tests for ListExpiredSandboxes\n- [ ] AC018: Unit tests for ListInactiveSandboxes\n- [ ] AC019: Unit tests for UpdateSessionLastActivity\n- [ ] AC020: Unit tests for Close\n\n### Picod Module\n- [ ] AC021: Unit tests for Server creation with valid and invalid configs\n- [ ] AC022: Unit tests for setWorkspace\n- [ ] AC023: Unit tests for sanitizePath with various path inputs\n- [ ] AC024: Unit tests for AuthManager LoadPublicKeyFromEnv, ValidateToken\n- [ ] AC025: Unit tests for auth middleware with public/protected paths\n- [ ] AC026: Unit tests for ExecuteHandler with valid commands, timeout, invalid working dir\n- [ ] AC027: Unit tests for UploadFileHandler, ListFilesHandler, DownloadFileHandler\n- [ ] AC028: Unit tests for HealthCheckHandler\n- [ ] AC029: Unit tests for LoadRSAPublicKey\n- [ ] AC030: Existing tests in router, store, picod packages remain passing\n\n---\n\n## Test File Status\n\n| Source File | Test File | Status |\n|-------------|-----------|--------|\n| router/server.go | server_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| router/config.go | config_test.go | Complete |\n| router/route.go | route_test.go | Complete |\n| router/backend.go | backend_test.go | Complete |\n| router/health.go | health_test.go | Complete |\n| router/ratelimit.go | ratelimit_test.go | Complete |\n| router/auth.go | auth_test.go | Complete |\n| router/session.go | session_test.go | Complete |\n| router/jwt.go | jwt_test.go | Complete |\n| router/logging.go | logging_test.go | Complete |\n| router/metrics.go | (uses existing) | N/A |\n| store/store.go | (interface only) | N/A |\n| store/store_valkey.go | store_valkey_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| store/store_redis.go | store_redis_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| picod/server.go | server_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| picod/execute.go | execute_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| picod/auth.go | auth_test.go | Complete |\n| picod/files.go | files_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| picod/health.go | health_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n\n---\n\n## Testing Patterns\n\n### Mocking Strategy\n- Use interfaces for dependencies (Store, HTTP clients, etc.)\n- Create mock implementations for testing using testify/mock\n- Use gomock or testify.mock for generating mocks\n\n### Test File Naming\n- Follow Go convention: `*_test.go`\n- Keep tests in same package as code under test\n- Use `package router` (not `package router_test`)\n\n### Table-Driven Tests\n- Use table-driven tests for parameterized scenarios\n- Example pattern:\n```go\ntests := []struct {\n    name    string\n    input   string\n    want    string\n    wantErr bool\n}{...}\n```\n\n### Test Coverage Goals\n- Router module: 70%+ code coverage\n- Store module: 80%+ code coverage\n- Picod module: 70%+ code coverage\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Router module: `pkg/router/`\n- Store module: `pkg/store/`\n- Picod module: `pkg/picod/`\n- Common types: `pkg/common/types/`\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the CLI pack command in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-020\n- **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe `pack` command is the first step in the AgentCube workflow. It validates the workspace structure, loads or creates agent metadata, processes dependencies, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and prepares the workspace for subsequent build and publish steps.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### AR-020-001: Workspace validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate that the workspace path exists and contains valid agent source files based on the specified language.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-001-A — Valid Python workspace\n\n- **GIVEN** a workspace directory exists at the specified path\n- **WHEN** `pack` is executed with a Python agent (default language)\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL validate that at least one `*.py` file exists in the workspace root\n- **AND** the workspace SHALL be considered valid for packaging\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-001-B — Valid Java workspace\n\n- **GIVEN** a workspace directory exists at the specified path\n- **WHEN** `pack` is executed with `--language java`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL validate that `pom.xml` exists in the workspace root\n- **AND** the workspace SHALL be considered valid for packaging\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-001-C — Missing workspace directory\n\n- **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist or is not a directory\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message indicating the directory does not exist\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-001-D — Python workspace without Python files\n\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` resolves to `\"python\"` (default)\n- **WHEN** no `*.py` file exists in the workspace root\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-001-E — Java workspace without pom.xml\n\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"`\n- **WHEN** `pom.xml` does not exist in the workspace root\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No pom.xml found in workspace\")`\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-002: Metadata loading and merging\n\nThe system SHALL load existing agent metadata from the workspace and merge CLI option overrides to create a complete metadata configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-002-A — Load existing metadata\n\n- **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` exists in the workspace\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL load the metadata using `MetadataService.load_metadata`\n- **AND** return an `AgentMetadata` object with all fields populated\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-002-B — Fallback metadata file loading\n\n- **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` does NOT exist in the workspace\n- **WHEN** metadata loading is attempted\n- **THEN** the system SHALL attempt to load `agent.yaml`, then `metadata.yaml` as fallbacks\n- **AND** raise `FileNotFoundError` if none of the fallback files exist\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-002-C — Create new metadata with defaults\n\n- **GIVEN** no metadata file exists in the workspace\n- **WHEN** `_load_or_create_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create a new `AgentMetadata` with default values:\n  - `language`: `\"python\"`\n  - `port`: `8080`\n  - `build_mode`: `\"local\"`\n  - `requirements_file`: `\"requirements.txt\"`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-002-D — CLI option overrides\n\n- **GIVEN** existing metadata and CLI options are provided\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._apply_option_overrides` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL override metadata fields with CLI-provided values:\n  - `--agent-name` overrides `agent_name`\n  - `--language` overrides `language`\n  - `--entrypoint` overrides `entrypoint`\n  - `--port` overrides `port`\n  - `--build-mode` overrides `build_mode`\n  - `--description` overrides `description`\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-003: Dockerfile generation\n\nThe system SHALL generate a Dockerfile in the workspace when packaging Python or Java agents.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-003-A — Generate Python Dockerfile\n\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"python\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL generate a Dockerfile using `_generate_python_dockerfile`\n- **AND** the Dockerfile SHALL include Python base image, dependency installation, entrypoint, and port exposure\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-003-B — Generate Java Dockerfile\n\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL generate a Dockerfile using `_generate_java_dockerfile`\n- **AND** the Dockerfile SHALL include Maven/Java base image, dependency installation, entrypoint, and port exposure\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-003-C — Skip Dockerfile when already exists\n\n- **GIVEN** a `Dockerfile` already exists in the workspace\n- **WHEN** `_generate_dockerfile` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL NOT overwrite the existing Dockerfile\n- **AND** return `None` indicating no new Dockerfile was generated\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-004: Dependency processing\n\nThe system SHALL process agent dependencies based on the language.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-004-A — Process Python dependencies\n\n- **GIVEN** `requirements.txt` exists in a Python workspace\n- **WHEN** `_process_python_dependencies` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL validate the requirements file format\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-004-B — Process Java dependencies\n\n- **GIVEN** `pom.xml` exists in a Java workspace\n- **WHEN** `_process_java_dependencies` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL validate the POM file exists\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-004-C — Missing Python requirements file\n\n- **GIVEN** workspace language is Python but `requirements.txt` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `_process_python_dependencies` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL log a warning but continue (requirements are optional)\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-005: Output preparation\n\nThe system SHALL prepare the output path for the packaged workspace.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-005-A — Default output path\n\n- **GIVEN** `--output` is not specified\n- **WHEN** `_prepare_output_path` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the original workspace path as the output\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-005-B — Custom output path\n\n- **GIVEN** `--output` specifies a custom directory path\n- **WHEN** `_prepare_output_path` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create the output directory if it does not exist\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-005-C — Update metadata after packaging\n\n- **GIVEN** packaging completes successfully\n- **WHEN** `_update_pack_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL save the final `AgentMetadata` to `{output_path}/agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-006: CLI interface\n\nThe system SHALL expose the `pack` command via Typer with specific options.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-006-A — Pack command options\n\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube pack --help`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL display:\n  - `-f, --workspace PATH` — Path to agent workspace (default: \".\")\n  - `--agent-name NAME` — Override agent name\n  - `--language LANG` — Programming language (python, java)\n  - `--entrypoint CMD` — Override entrypoint command\n  - `--port PORT` — Port to expose (default: 8080)\n  - `--build-mode MODE` — Build strategy (local, cloud)\n  - `--description TEXT` — Agent description\n  - `--output PATH` — Output path for packaged workspace\n  - `--verbose` — Enable detailed logging\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-006-B — Successful pack output\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid workspace with all required files\n- **WHEN** `pack` completes without exception\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print success message using Rich `Progress` spinner\n- **AND** display agent name, resolved workspace path, and metadata file path\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-006-C — Pack failure with verbose logging\n\n- **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n- **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is enabled\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red with full traceback\n- **AND** exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-006-D — Pack failure without verbose\n\n- **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n- **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is NOT enabled\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red without traceback\n- **AND** exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-007: Language compatibility validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate that the specified language and port are valid.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-007-A — Valid language specification\n\n- **GIVEN** `--language` is provided as `\"python\"` or `\"java\"` (case-insensitive)\n- **WHEN** `_validate_language_compatibility` runs\n- **THEN** the validation SHALL pass successfully\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-007-B — Invalid language specification\n\n- **GIVEN** `--language` is provided as an unsupported value\n- **WHEN** Pydantic validator runs on the metadata\n- **THEN** validation SHALL fail with `ValueError` indicating valid options are `python` or `java`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-007-C — Port range validation\n\n- **GIVEN** `--port` is provided with a value outside valid range\n- **WHEN** Pydantic validator runs on the metadata\n- **THEN** validation SHALL fail with `ValueError` indicating port must be between 1 and 65535\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-008: Entrypoint inference\n\nThe system SHALL infer the entrypoint command if not explicitly provided.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-008-A — Infer Python entrypoint\n\n- **GIVEN** `--entrypoint` is not provided for a Python agent\n- **WHEN** `_infer_entrypoint` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL look for `main.py` in the workspace root\n- **AND** default to `python main.py` if found\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-008-B — Infer Java entrypoint\n\n- **GIVEN** `--entrypoint` is not provided for a Java agent\n- **WHEN** `_infer_entrypoint` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL look for a main class in `pom.xml`\n- **AND** default to `java -jar target/*.jar` if a JAR is expected\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC001: Pack validates workspace structure before processing\n- [ ] AC002: Pack loads or creates metadata with proper defaults\n- [ ] AC003: Pack merges CLI option overrides into metadata\n- [ ] AC004: Pack generates Dockerfile when needed (Python/Java)\n- [ ] AC005: Pack processes dependencies for the target language\n- [ ] AC006: Pack prepares output path and saves metadata\n- [ ] AC007: Pack displays success output with Rich formatting\n- [ ] AC008: Pack handles errors with proper exit codes and verbose logging\n- [ ] AC009: Pack validates language and port values\n- [ ] AC010: Pack infers entrypoint when not provided\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Notes\n\n### Key Components\n\n| Component | Path | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| CLI Entry | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer app with `pack` command |\n| PackRuntime | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Core packaging logic |\n| MetadataService | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Metadata CRUD operations |\n| AgentMetadata | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Pydantic model for agent config |\n| DockerService | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Dockerfile generation and Docker operations |\n\n### Metadata Fields (AgentMetadata)\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| agent_name | str | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n| language | str | \"python\" | Programming language used |\n| entrypoint | str | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n| port | int | 8080 | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n| build_mode | str | \"local\" | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n| description | Optional[str] | None | Human-readable summary |\n| requirements_file | Optional[str] | \"requirements.txt\" | Python dependency file |\n\n### CLI Options Mapping\n\n| CLI Option | Metadata Field | Type |\n|------------|----------------|------|\n| `--agent-name` | agent_name | Optional[str] |\n| `--language` | language | Optional[str] |\n| `--entrypoint` | entrypoint | Optional[str] |\n| `--port` | port | Optional[int] |\n| `--build-mode` | build_mode | Optional[str] |\n| `--description` | description | Optional[str] |\n| `--output` | (output path) | Optional[str] |\n\n---\n\n# Delta Spec: AR-038 — Go Unit Testing (workloadmanager)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing Go unit tests for the workloadmanager module (`pkg/workloadmanager`).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-038\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: L\n\n## Reference\n\nBase spec: client-go library from `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe workloadmanager module provides workload management for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources in Kubernetes. It includes:\n- WorkloadManager interface for CRUD operations\n- GC (Garbage Collection) worker for expired resource cleanup\n- Expiration checker for TTL and idle timeout\n- Graceful manager for connection draining\n- Cleanup manager for orphaned resources\n- Batch manager for bulk operations\n- HTTP server with REST API endpoints\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Feature: CleanupManager Resource Cleanup\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-001-A — CleanupManager deletes orphaned services\n\n- **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n- **WHEN** cleanupServices is called with a namespace and owner reference\n- **THEN** it should return a list of cleaned service resource strings\n- **AND** services with matching owner references should be deleted\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-001-B — CleanupManager deletes orphaned configmaps\n\n- **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n- **WHEN** cleanupConfigMaps is called with a namespace and owner reference\n- **THEN** it should return a list of cleaned configmap resource strings\n- **AND** configmaps with the annotation `agentcube.volcano.sh/auto-delete=true` and matching owner should be deleted\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-001-C — CleanupManager handles retained PVCs\n\n- **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n- **WHEN** cleanupPVCs is called with a namespace and owner reference for a PVC with Retain policy\n- **THEN** the PVC should not be deleted\n- **AND** other PVCs with matching owner should be deleted\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-001-D — CleanupManager cleans orphaned resources\n\n- **GIVEN** a CleanupManager and a Sandbox object\n- **WHEN** cleanupOrphanedResources is called\n- **THEN** it should clean services, configmaps, and PVCs associated with the sandbox\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-001-E — CleanupManager finds orphaned services\n\n- **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n- **WHEN** FindOrphanedServices is called with namespace and sessionID\n- **THEN** it should return service names that have no owner references\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-001-F — CleanupManager CleanupAllResources\n\n- **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n- **WHEN** CleanupAllResources is called with a sandbox\n- **THEN** it should clean all associated resources\n\n---\n\n### Feature: BatchManager Operations\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-002-A — BatchManager deletes all sandboxes synchronously under threshold\n\n- **GIVEN** a BatchManager with workloadMgr and gracefulMgr\n- **WHEN** handleDeleteAllSandboxes is called with fewer than AsyncThreshold (10) sandboxes\n- **THEN** it should delete all sandboxes synchronously\n- **AND** return a BatchDeleteResponse with deleted and failed counts\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-002-B — BatchManager deletes all sandboxes asynchronously over threshold\n\n- **GIVEN** a BatchManager with workloadMgr and gracefulMgr\n- **WHEN** handleDeleteAllSandboxes is called with more than AsyncThreshold (10) sandboxes\n- **THEN** it should start async deletion in background\n- **AND** return immediately with all items marked as deleted\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-002-C — BatchManager deletes stale sandboxes\n\n- **GIVEN** a BatchManager with workloadMgr and gracefulMgr\n- **WHEN** deleteStaleSandboxes is called\n- **THEN** it should delete all sandboxes in Unknown or Failed state older than StaleStateThreshold (1 hour)\n- **AND** return a BatchDeleteResponse with results\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-002-D — BatchManager deletes by label selector\n\n- **GIVEN** a BatchManager with workloadMgr and gracefulMgr\n- **WHEN** handleDeleteByLabelSelector is called with a label selector\n- **THEN** it should delete all sandboxes matching the label selector\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-002-E — BatchManager public methods\n\n- **GIVEN** a BatchManager\n- **WHEN** DeleteAllInNamespace, DeleteByLabelSelector, or DeleteStaleSandboxes are called\n- **THEN** they should delegate to the appropriate handler methods\n\n---\n\n### Feature: WorkloadManager Sandbox Operations\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-A — GetSandboxBySessionID finds AgentRuntime\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client that has AgentRuntime resources\n- **WHEN** GetSandboxBySessionID is called with a sessionID that exists in an AgentRuntime\n- **THEN** it should return a Sandbox object with correct fields\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-B — GetSandboxBySessionID finds CodeInterpreter\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client that has CodeInterpreter resources\n- **WHEN** GetSandboxBySessionID is called with a sessionID that exists in a CodeInterpreter\n- **THEN** it should return a Sandbox object with correct fields\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-C — GetSandboxBySessionID returns error when not found\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client\n- **WHEN** GetSandboxBySessionID is called with a non-existent sessionID\n- **THEN** it should return ErrSandboxNotFound\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-D — DeleteSandbox deletes AgentRuntime by sessionId\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client that has AgentRuntime with matching sessionId label\n- **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called with namespace, sessionID, and delete options\n- **THEN** it should delete the matching AgentRuntime\n- **AND** return nil on success\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-E — DeleteSandbox deletes CodeInterpreter by sessionId\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client that has CodeInterpreter with matching sessionId label\n- **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called with namespace, sessionID, and delete options\n- **THEN** it should delete the matching CodeInterpreter\n- **AND** return nil on success\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-F — DeleteSandbox applies force delete\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client\n- **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called with Force=true\n- **THEN** it should set GracePeriodSeconds to 0\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-G — DeleteSandbox applies label selector\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client\n- **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called with LabelSelector\n- **THEN** it should use the label selector when listing resources\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-H — ListSandboxes returns combined list\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client that has both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n- **WHEN** ListSandboxes is called with namespace and ListOptions\n- **THEN** it should return a SandboxList containing both types\n- **AND** apply label and field selectors correctly\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Server HTTP Handlers\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-004-A — Server health check endpoint\n\n- **GIVEN** a Server instance\n- **WHEN** GET /healthz is requested\n- **THEN** it should return HTTP 200 with \"ok\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-004-B — Server readiness check - ready\n\n- **GIVEN** a Server with ready=true\n- **WHEN** GET /readyz is requested\n- **THEN** it should return HTTP 200 with status \"ok\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-004-C — Server readiness check - not ready\n\n- **GIVEN** a Server with ready=false\n- **WHEN** GET /readyz is requested\n- **THEN** it should return HTTP 503 with status \"not ready\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-004-D — Server starts and stops cleanly\n\n- **GIVEN** a Server with valid config\n- **WHEN** Start() is called\n- **THEN** it should bind to the configured port\n- **AND** Start() should return nil\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-004-E — Server handles API error mapping\n\n- **GIVEN** a Server with a WorkloadManager that returns an error\n- **WHEN** handleError is called with k8s IsNotFound error\n- **THEN** it should return HTTP 404 with reason \"NotFound\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-004-F — Server corsMiddleware sets headers\n\n- **GIVEN** a Server\n- **WHEN** corsMiddleware processes a request\n- **THEN** it should set Access-Control-Allow-* headers\n- **AND** handle OPTIONS preflight requests\n\n---\n\n### Feature: GracefulManager Operations\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-A — GracefulManager registers connection\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager\n- **WHEN** RegisterConnection is called with a sandboxID\n- **THEN** the active connection count should increment\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-B — GracefulManager unregisters connection\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager with an active connection\n- **WHEN** UnregisterConnection is called with the sandboxID\n- **THEN** the active connection count should decrement\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-C — GracefulManager drains connections\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager\n- **WHEN** drainConnections is called with a sandboxID\n- **THEN** the draining flag should be set to true\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-D — GracefulManager checks if draining\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager with a sandbox marked for draining\n- **WHEN** IsDraining is called with the sandboxID\n- **THEN** it should return true\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-E — GracefulManager gets active connections\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager with registered connections\n- **WHEN** GetActiveConnections is called\n- **THEN** it should return the correct count\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-F — GracefulManager cleans up sandbox state\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager with a sandbox\n- **WHEN** Cleanup is called with the sandboxID\n- **THEN** the sandbox entry should be removed from connections map\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-G — GracefulManager waitForConnections timeout\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager with active connections that never drain\n- **WHEN** waitForConnections is called with a short timeout\n- **THEN** it should return an error after timeout\n\n---\n\n### Feature: K8sClient Initialization\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-006-A — K8sClient NewK8sClient with kubeconfig path\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid kubeconfig path\n- **WHEN** NewK8sClient is called with the path\n- **THEN** it should return a K8sClient with Clientset, KubernetesClient, and DynamicClient\n- **AND** return nil error\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-006-B — K8sClient NewK8sClient with in-cluster mode\n\n- **GIVEN** InClusterMode constant\n- **WHEN** NewK8sClient is called with InClusterMode\n- **THEN** it should attempt in-cluster config\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-006-C — K8sClient NewInClusterClient\n\n- **GIVEN** running inside a Kubernetes cluster\n- **WHEN** NewInClusterClient is called\n- **THEN** it should create clients using in-cluster config\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-006-D — K8sClient expandKubeconfigPath handles tilde\n\n- **GIVEN** a path starting with ~\n- **WHEN** expandKubeconfigPath is called\n- **THEN** it should replace ~ with the home directory\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-006-E — K8sClient expandKubeconfigPath handles empty path\n\n- **GIVEN** an empty string\n- **WHEN** expandKubeconfigPath is called\n- **THEN** it should return the empty string\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Type Helper Functions\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-007-A — NewAPIResponse creates correct response\n\n- **GIVEN** data and metadata\n- **WHEN** NewAPIResponse is called\n- **THEN** it should return an APIResponse with Status=\"Success\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-007-B — NewAPIError creates correct error\n\n- **GIVEN** message, reason, and code\n- **WHEN** NewAPIError is called\n- **THEN** it should return an APIError with Status=\"Failure\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-007-C — sandboxFromAgentRuntime maps running state\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with Running condition\n- **WHEN** sandboxFromAgentRuntime is called\n- **THEN** the returned Sandbox should have State=SandboxStateRunning\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-007-D — sandboxFromAgentRuntime maps failed state\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with Failed condition\n- **WHEN** sandboxFromAgentRuntime is called\n- **THEN** the returned Sandbox should have State=SandboxStateFailed\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-007-E — sandboxFromAgentRuntime maps deleting state\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with DeletionTimestamp\n- **WHEN** sandboxFromAgentRuntime is called\n- **THEN** the returned Sandbox should have State=SandboxStateDeleting\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-007-F — sandboxFromCodeInterpreter maps running state\n\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with Ready=true\n- **WHEN** sandboxFromCodeInterpreter is called\n- **THEN** the returned Sandbox should have State=SandboxStateRunning\n\n---\n\n### Feature: ListExpiredSandboxes\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-008-A — ListExpiredSandboxes returns expired AgentRuntimes\n\n- **GIVEN** a client with AgentRuntime resources\n- **WHEN** ListExpiredSandboxes is called\n- **THEN** it should return sandboxes that have expired\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-008-B — ListExpiredSandboxes returns expired CodeInterpreters\n\n- **GIVEN** a client with CodeInterpreter resources\n- **WHEN** ListExpiredSandboxes is called\n- **THEN** it should return sandboxes that have expired\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-008-C — ListExpiredSandboxes handles empty namespace\n\n- **GIVEN** a client with resources in a namespace\n- **WHEN** ListExpiredSandboxes is called with an empty namespace string\n- **THEN** it should list all expired sandboxes\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Retry Logic\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-009-A — Retry with exponential backoff\n\n- **GIVEN** a function that fails initially then succeeds\n- **WHEN** retry logic is applied\n- **THEN** it should retry with increasing delays\n- **AND** ultimately succeed\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-009-B — Retry stops after max attempts\n\n- **GIVEN** a function that always fails\n- **WHEN** retry logic is applied with max attempts\n- **THEN** it should return the last error after exhausting retries\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC001: All CleanupManager methods must have unit tests covering success and error paths\n- [ ] AC002: All BatchManager methods must have tests with mocked WorkloadManager\n- [ ] AC003: WorkloadManager sandbox operations must have tests with fake clients\n- [ ] AC004: Server HTTP handlers must have tests using httptest\n- [ ] AC005: GracefulManager connection tracking must have unit tests\n- [ ] AC006: K8sClient initialization must have tests for different config modes\n- [ ] AC007: Helper functions (NewAPIResponse, NewAPIError, sandboxFrom*) must have tests\n- [ ] AC008: ListExpiredSandboxes must have tests for both resource types\n- [ ] AC009: Retry logic must have unit tests for backoff behavior\n- [ ] AC010: Existing tests in service_test.go, gc_test.go, expiration_test.go remain passing\n\n---\n\n## Test File Status\n\n| Source File | Test File | Status |\n|-------------|-----------|--------|\n| service.go | service_test.go | Complete |\n| gc.go | gc_test.go | Complete |\n| expiration.go | expiration_test.go | Complete |\n| cleanup.go | cleanup_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| server.go | server_test.go | Complete |\n| graceful.go | graceful_test.go | Complete |\n| batch.go | batch_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| client.go | client_test.go | Complete |\n| delete_test.go | N/A | Exists |\n| retry.go | retry_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Client-go library: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n- API Group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh / v1alpha1`\n- Resources: AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter","after":"# Delta Spec: AR-039 — Go Unit Testing (router/store/picod)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing Go unit tests for three core modules: router, store, and picod.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-039\n- **Module**: `pkg`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: L\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe agentcube project consists of three main modules requiring unit tests:\n\n1. **pkg/router**: HTTP routing, proxy, health checking, rate limiting, authentication, session management, JWT\n2. **pkg/store**: Valkey/Redis-backed session and sandbox storage\n3. **pkg/picod**: Pico execution server with command execution and file handling\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Feature: Router Module - Initialization and Configuration\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-001-A — Router creates with default config\n\n- **GIVEN** a nil config is passed to `NewRouter`\n- **WHEN** `NewRouter(config)` is called\n- **THEN** a Router instance is returned with default configuration values\n- **AND** default listen address is \":8080\"\n- **AND** backend timeout is 30 seconds\n- **AND** rate limiting is disabled by default\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-001-B — Router creates with custom config\n\n- **GIVEN** a Config with SessionEnabled=true and JWTEnabled=true\n- **WHEN** `NewRouter(config)` is called\n- **THEN** a Router instance is returned with SessionManager initialized\n- **AND** JWTManager is initialized\n- **AND** SessionHandler is registered for /v1/sessions\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-001-C — Router adds and removes backends\n\n- **GIVEN** a Router instance is created\n- **WHEN** `AddBackend(\"backend1\", \"http://localhost:8081\", \"/api\", \"backend-1\")` is called\n- **THEN** the backend is added to the pool\n- **WHEN** `RemoveBackend(\"backend1\")` is called\n- **THEN** the backend is removed from the pool\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Router Module - Backend Pool and Health Checking\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-002-A — Backend pool routes requests\n\n- **GIVEN** a BackendPool with multiple backends registered\n- **WHEN** `GetBackendForRequest()` is called with a path matching a backend prefix\n- **THEN** the matching backend is returned\n- **WHEN** `GetBackendForRequest()` is called with a non-matching path\n- **THEN** nil is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-002-B — Health checker monitors backends\n\n- **GIVEN** a BackendPool with registered backends\n- **WHEN** HealthChecker Start() is invoked\n- **THEN** periodic health checks run at configured interval\n- **WHEN** a backend becomes unhealthy\n- **THEN** the backend is marked as unavailable\n- **WHEN** HealthChecker Stop() is invoked\n- **THEN** health checking stops\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Router Module - Rate Limiting\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-003-A — Rate limiter allows requests under limit\n\n- **GIVEN** RateLimiter with RPS=10 and Burst=20\n- **WHEN** 5 requests arrive in quick succession\n- **THEN** all requests are allowed through\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-003-B — Rate limiter blocks requests over limit\n\n- **GIVEN** RateLimiter with RPS=2 and Burst=4\n- **WHEN** 10 requests arrive simultaneously\n- **THEN** requests beyond burst limit are blocked with 429 status\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-003-C — Rate limiter can be disabled\n\n- **GIVEN** RateLimiter with enabled=false\n- **WHEN** any number of requests arrive\n- **THEN** all requests pass through without rate limiting\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Router Module - Authentication\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-004-A — Authenticator validates token\n\n- **GIVEN** Authenticator with AuthEnabled=true and AuthToken=\"secret\"\n- **WHEN** request with \"Authorization: Bearer secret\" header arrives\n- **THEN** request is allowed\n- **WHEN** request with wrong token arrives\n- **THEN** request is rejected with 401 status\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-004-B — Authenticator can be disabled\n\n- **GIVEN** Authenticator with AuthEnabled=false\n- **WHEN** any request arrives\n- **THEN** request passes through without token validation\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Router Module - Session Management\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-005-A — Session manager creates session\n\n- **GIVEN** SessionManager with SessionEnabled=true\n- **WHEN** a new session is created via session store\n- **THEN** session ID is generated\n- **AND** session data is stored with expiry\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-005-B — Session manager cleanup removes expired sessions\n\n- **GIVEN** SessionManager with sessions in store\n- **WHEN** cleanup runs and finds expired sessions\n- **THEN** expired sessions are removed from store\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-005-C — Session middleware attaches session to request\n\n- **GIVEN** a request with valid session cookie\n- **WHEN** request passes through SessionMiddleware\n- **THEN** session info is available in request context\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Router Module - JWT Authentication\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-006-A — JWT manager creates token\n\n- **GIVEN** JWTManager configured with HS256 algorithm and secret=\"mysecret\"\n- **WHEN** `GenerateToken(claims)` is called with user claims\n- **THEN** a signed JWT token is returned\n- **AND** token contains correct issuer and audience\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-006-B — JWT manager validates token\n\n- **GIVEN** JWTManager configured with valid secret\n- **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called with a valid token\n- **THEN** claims are returned without error\n- **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called with an expired token\n- **THEN** error is returned indicating token expiration\n- **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called with invalid signature\n- **THEN** error is returned indicating invalid token\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-006-C — JWT middleware enforces authentication\n\n- **GIVEN** JWTMiddleware with JWTEnabled=true and JWTAllowQueryParam=false\n- **WHEN** request without JWT arrives at protected endpoint\n- **THEN** request is rejected with 401 status\n- **WHEN** request with valid JWT in Authorization header arrives\n- **THEN** request is allowed and claims available in context\n- **WHEN** JWTAllowQueryParam=true and JWT in query param\n- **THEN** request is allowed\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Router Module - Logging and Metrics\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-007-A — Logger records requests\n\n- **GIVEN** Logger middleware is in the chain\n- **WHEN** HTTP request arrives\n- **THEN** request details are logged including method, path, duration\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-007-B — Metrics records request stats\n\n- **GIVEN** Metrics instance\n- **WHEN** `IncBackendRequests(backend, status)` is called\n- **THEN** backend request counter increments\n- **WHEN** `RecordRequestDuration(method, path, backend, duration)` is called\n- **THEN** request duration is recorded\n- **WHEN** `IncErrors(errorType)` is called\n- **THEN** error counter increments\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Store Module - Store Interface\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-008-A — Store interface contract\n\n- **GIVEN** a Store implementation (Valkey or Redis)\n- **WHEN** all interface methods are called\n- **THEN** the Store implements the complete Store interface:\n  - Ping() error\n  - GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n  - StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error\n  - UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error\n  - DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) error\n  - ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n  - ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n  - UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at) error\n  - Close() error\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Store Module - Valkey Store\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-A — Valkey store connects with credentials\n\n- **GIVEN** environment variables VALKEY_ADDR and VALKEY_PASSWORD are set\n- **WHEN** `newValkeyStore()` is called\n- **THEN** a Valkey client connects successfully\n- **AND** ping returns \"PONG\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-B — Valkey store requires address\n\n- **GIVEN** VALKEY_ADDR is not set\n- **WHEN** `newValkeyStore()` is called\n- **THEN** error is returned indicating VALKEY_ADDR is required\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-C — Valkey store stores sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid SandboxInfo with SessionID and ExpiresAt\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** sandbox is stored in Valkey\n- **AND** session is added to expiry index\n- **AND** session is added to last activity index\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-D — Valkey store retrieves sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox was previously stored\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` is called\n- **THEN** correct SandboxInfo is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-E — Valkey store returns error for non-existent session\n\n- **GIVEN** a session ID that doesn't exist\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` is called\n- **THEN** ErrNotFound is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-F — Valkey store updates sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox exists in store\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** sandbox data is updated\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-G — Valkey store deletes sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox exists in store\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` is called\n- **THEN** sandbox is removed from store\n- **AND** session is removed from expiry index\n- **AND** session is removed from last activity index\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-H — Valkey store lists expired sandboxes\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple sandboxes with different expiry times\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** only sandboxes expiring before 'before' are returned\n- **AND** maximum of 'limit' results are returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-I — Valkey store lists inactive sandboxes\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple sandboxes with different last activity times\n- **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** only sandboxes inactive before 'before' are returned\n- **AND** maximum of 'limit' results are returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-J — Valkey store validates input\n\n- **GIVEN** nil sandbox passed to StoreSandbox\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n- **THEN** error \"sandbox is nil\" is returned\n\n- **GIVEN** sandbox with zero ExpiresAt\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** error \"invalid expiry: ExpiresAt is zero\" is returned\n\n- **GIVEN** sandbox with empty SessionID\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** error \"session ID is required\" is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-K — Valkey store updates last activity\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox exists in store\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, time)` is called\n- **THEN** last activity timestamp is updated in index\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-L — Valkey store closes connection\n\n- **GIVEN** a Valkey store is connected\n- **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n- **THEN** connection is closed\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Picod Module - Server Initialization\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-010-A — Server creates with valid config\n\n- **GIVEN** valid Config and AuthConfig\n- **WHEN** `NewServer(config, authConfig)` is called\n- **THEN** server instance is returned\n- **AND** Gin engine is configured\n- **AND** routes are registered\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-010-B — Server validates config\n\n- **GIVEN** Config with invalid values (e.g., negative port)\n- **WHEN** `NewServer(config, authConfig)` is called\n- **THEN** error is returned indicating invalid config\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-010-C — Server sets workspace directory\n\n- **GIVEN** Config with Workspace=\"/tmp/test-workspace\"\n- **WHEN** Server initializes\n- **THEN** workspace directory is created if not exists\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-010-D — Server creates with empty workspace\n\n- **GIVEN** Config with empty Workspace\n- **WHEN** Server initializes\n- **THEN** current working directory is used as workspace\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Picod Module - Path Sanitization\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-011-A — Path sanitization allows safe paths\n\n- **GIVEN** Server with workspace=\"/app\"\n- **WHEN** `sanitizePath(\"subdir/file.txt\")` is called\n- **THEN** resolved path within workspace is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-011-B — Path sanitization blocks escape attempts\n\n- **GIVEN** Server with workspace=\"/app\"\n- **WHEN** `sanitizePath(\"../../../etc/passwd\")` is called\n- **THEN** error \"access denied: path escapes workspace\" is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-011-C — Path sanitization blocks absolute paths\n\n- **GIVEN** Server with workspace=\"/app\"\n- **WHEN** `sanitizePath(\"/etc/passwd\")` is called\n- **THEN** error \"access denied: path escapes workspace\" is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-011-D — Path sanitization handles symlinks\n\n- **GIVEN** Server with workspace=\"/app\" and symlink /app/link -> /tmp\n- **WHEN** `sanitizePath(\"link/sensitive\")` is called\n- **THEN** error \"access denied: path escapes workspace\" is returned\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Picod Module - Authentication\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-012-A — Auth manager loads public key\n\n- **GIVEN** AuthConfig with valid RSA public key in PEM format\n- **WHEN** AuthManager initializes\n- **THEN** public key is loaded successfully\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-012-B — Auth manager validates JWT\n\n- **GIVEN** AuthManager with loaded public key\n- **WHEN** valid JWT token is validated\n- **THEN** claims are returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-012-C — Auth manager rejects invalid JWT\n\n- **GIVEN** AuthManager with loaded public key\n- **WHEN** invalid or expired JWT token is validated\n- **THEN** error is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-012-D — Auth middleware allows public paths\n\n- **GIVEN** request to public path like /health\n- **WHEN** request passes through auth middleware\n- **THEN** request is allowed without JWT validation\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-012-E — Auth middleware requires auth for protected paths\n\n- **GIVEN** request to protected path /api/execute without token\n- **WHEN** request passes through auth middleware\n- **THEN** request is rejected with 401\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Picod Module - Execute Handler\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-013-A — Execute handler runs valid command\n\n- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with Command=[\"echo\", \"hello\"]\n- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n- **THEN** response with stdout=\"hello\", ExitCode=0 is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-013-B — Execute handler fails on empty command\n\n- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with empty Command array\n- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n- **THEN** error response with code 400 is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-013-C — Execute handler respects timeout\n\n- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with Command=[\"sleep\", \"10\"] and Timeout=\"1s\"\n- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n- **THEN** response with ExitCode=124 (timeout) is returned\n- **AND** stderr indicates timeout\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-013-D — Execute handler validates working directory\n\n- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with WorkingDir=\"../../../etc\"\n- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n- **THEN** error response with code 400 is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-013-E — Execute handler captures stderr\n\n- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with Command=[\"ls\", \"/nonexistent\"]\n- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n- **THEN** response includes stderr output\n- **AND** non-zero ExitCode is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-013-F — Execute handler accepts custom environment\n\n- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with Command=[\"env\"] and Env={\"TEST_VAR\": \"test\"}\n- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n- **THEN** response stdout contains TEST_VAR=test\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Picod Module - File Handlers\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-014-A — Upload file handler saves file\n\n- **GIVEN** file upload request with valid content\n- **WHEN** UploadFileHandler processes request\n- **THEN** file is saved to workspace\n- **AND** success response is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-014-B — List files handler returns directory contents\n\n- **GIVEN** workspace with multiple files\n- **WHEN** ListFilesHandler is called\n- **THEN** list of files is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-014-C — Download file handler serves file\n\n- **GIVEN** file exists in workspace\n- **WHEN** DownloadFileHandler is called with path\n- **THEN** file content is served\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-014-D — Download file handler blocks path escape\n\n- **GIVEN** request for file outside workspace\n- **WHEN** DownloadFileHandler processes request\n- **THEN** request is rejected\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Picod Module - Health Check and RSA Key Loading\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-015-A — Health check returns healthy status\n\n- **GIVEN** Server is running\n- **WHEN** GET /health is requested\n- **THEN** response with status \"healthy\" is returned\n- **AND** HTTP 200 status code\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-015-B — LoadRSAPublicKey parses valid PEM\n\n- **GIVEN** valid RSA public key in PEM format\n- **WHEN** `LoadRSAPublicKey(pemData)` is called\n- **THEN** *rsa.PublicKey is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-015-C — LoadRSAPublicKey rejects invalid PEM\n\n- **GIVEN** invalid PEM data\n- **WHEN** `LoadRSAPublicKey(pemData)` is called\n- **THEN** error is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-015-D — LoadRSAPublicKey rejects non-RSA key\n\n- **GIVEN** PEM data containing non-RSA key\n- **WHEN** `LoadRSAPublicKey(pemData)` is called\n- **THEN** error \"public key is not an RSA key\" is returned\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n### Router Module\n- [ ] AC001: Unit tests for Config initialization and defaults\n- [ ] AC002: Unit tests for Router creation with various config combinations\n- [ ] AC003: Unit tests for BackendPool AddBackend, RemoveBackend, GetBackendForRequest\n- [ ] AC004: Unit tests for HealthChecker Start, Stop, checkBackend\n- [ ] AC005: Unit tests for RateLimiter Allow, Middleware\n- [ ] AC006: Unit tests for Authenticator Middleware with enabled/disabled states\n- [ ] AC007: Unit tests for SessionManager Create, Get, Delete, Cleanup\n- [ ] AC008: Unit tests for JWTManager GenerateToken, ValidateToken\n- [ ] AC009: Unit tests for JWTMiddleware with various configurations\n- [ ] AC010: Unit tests for Logger Middleware\n- [ ] AC011: Unit tests for Metrics IncBackendRequests, RecordRequestDuration, IncErrors\n\n### Store Module\n- [ ] AC012: Unit tests for Valkey store connection with mocked client\n- [ ] AC013: Unit tests for StoreSandbox with valid and invalid inputs\n- [ ] AC014: Unit tests for GetSandboxBySessionID with existing and non-existing sessions\n- [ ] AC015: Unit tests for UpdateSandbox\n- [ ] AC016: Unit tests for DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n- [ ] AC017: Unit tests for ListExpiredSandboxes\n- [ ] AC018: Unit tests for ListInactiveSandboxes\n- [ ] AC019: Unit tests for UpdateSessionLastActivity\n- [ ] AC020: Unit tests for Close\n\n### Picod Module\n- [ ] AC021: Unit tests for Server creation with valid and invalid configs\n- [ ] AC022: Unit tests for setWorkspace\n- [ ] AC023: Unit tests for sanitizePath with various path inputs\n- [ ] AC024: Unit tests for AuthManager LoadPublicKeyFromEnv, ValidateToken\n- [ ] AC025: Unit tests for auth middleware with public/protected paths\n- [ ] AC026: Unit tests for ExecuteHandler with valid commands, timeout, invalid working dir\n- [ ] AC027: Unit tests for UploadFileHandler, ListFilesHandler, DownloadFileHandler\n- [ ] AC028: Unit tests for HealthCheckHandler\n- [ ] AC029: Unit tests for LoadRSAPublicKey\n- [ ] AC030: Existing tests in router, store, picod packages remain passing\n\n---\n\n## Test File Status\n\n| Source File | Test File | Status |\n|-------------|-----------|--------|\n| router/server.go | server_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| router/config.go | config_test.go | Complete |\n| router/route.go | route_test.go | Complete |\n| router/backend.go | backend_test.go | Complete |\n| router/health.go | health_test.go | Complete |\n| router/ratelimit.go | ratelimit_test.go | Complete |\n| router/auth.go | auth_test.go | Complete |\n| router/session.go | session_test.go | Complete |\n| router/jwt.go | jwt_test.go | Complete |\n| router/logging.go | logging_test.go | Complete |\n| router/metrics.go | (uses existing) | N/A |\n| store/store.go | (interface only) | N/A |\n| store/store_valkey.go | store_valkey_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| store/store_redis.go | store_redis_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| picod/server.go | server_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| picod/execute.go | execute_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| picod/auth.go | auth_test.go | Complete |\n| picod/files.go | files_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| picod/health.go | health_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n\n---\n\n## Testing Patterns\n\n### Mocking Strategy\n- Use interfaces for dependencies (Store, HTTP clients, etc.)\n- Create mock implementations for testing using testify/mock\n- Use gomock or testify.mock for generating mocks\n\n### Test File Naming\n- Follow Go convention: `*_test.go`\n- Keep tests in same package as code under test\n- Use `package router` (not `package router_test`)\n\n### Table-Driven Tests\n- Use table-driven tests for parameterized scenarios\n- Example pattern:\n```go\ntests := []struct {\n    name    string\n    input   string\n    want    string\n    wantErr bool\n}{...}\n```\n\n### Test Coverage Goals\n- Router module: 70%+ code coverage\n- Store module: 80%+ code coverage\n- Picod module: 70%+ code coverage\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Router module: `pkg/router/`\n- Store module: `pkg/store/`\n- Picod module: `pkg/picod/`\n- Common types: `pkg/common/types/`\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the CLI pack command in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-020\n- **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe `pack` command is the first step in the AgentCube workflow. It validates the workspace structure, loads or creates agent metadata, processes dependencies, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and prepares the workspace for subsequent build and publish steps.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### AR-020-001: Workspace validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate that the workspace path exists and contains valid agent source files based on the specified language.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-001-A — Valid Python workspace\n\n- **GIVEN** a workspace directory exists at the specified path\n- **WHEN** `pack` is executed with a Python agent (default language)\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL validate that at least one `*.py` file exists in the workspace root\n- **AND** the workspace SHALL be considered valid for packaging\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-001-B — Valid Java workspace\n\n- **GIVEN** a workspace directory exists at the specified path\n- **WHEN** `pack` is executed with `--language java`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL validate that `pom.xml` exists in the workspace root\n- **AND** the workspace SHALL be considered valid for packaging\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-001-C — Missing workspace directory\n\n- **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist or is not a directory\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message indicating the directory does not exist\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-001-D — Python workspace without Python files\n\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` resolves to `\"python\"` (default)\n- **WHEN** no `*.py` file exists in the workspace root\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-001-E — Java workspace without pom.xml\n\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"`\n- **WHEN** `pom.xml` does not exist in the workspace root\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No pom.xml found in workspace\")`\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-002: Metadata loading and merging\n\nThe system SHALL load existing agent metadata from the workspace and merge CLI option overrides to create a complete metadata configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-002-A — Load existing metadata\n\n- **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` exists in the workspace\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL load the metadata using `MetadataService.load_metadata`\n- **AND** return an `AgentMetadata` object with all fields populated\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-002-B — Fallback metadata file loading\n\n- **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` does NOT exist in the workspace\n- **WHEN** metadata loading is attempted\n- **THEN** the system SHALL attempt to load `agent.yaml`, then `metadata.yaml` as fallbacks\n- **AND** raise `FileNotFoundError` if none of the fallback files exist\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-002-C — Create new metadata with defaults\n\n- **GIVEN** no metadata file exists in the workspace\n- **WHEN** `_load_or_create_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create a new `AgentMetadata` with default values:\n  - `language`: `\"python\"`\n  - `port`: `8080`\n  - `build_mode`: `\"local\"`\n  - `requirements_file`: `\"requirements.txt\"`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-002-D — CLI option overrides\n\n- **GIVEN** existing metadata and CLI options are provided\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._apply_option_overrides` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL override metadata fields with CLI-provided values:\n  - `--agent-name` overrides `agent_name`\n  - `--language` overrides `language`\n  - `--entrypoint` overrides `entrypoint`\n  - `--port` overrides `port`\n  - `--build-mode` overrides `build_mode`\n  - `--description` overrides `description`\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-003: Dockerfile generation\n\nThe system SHALL generate a Dockerfile in the workspace when packaging Python or Java agents.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-003-A — Generate Python Dockerfile\n\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"python\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL generate a Dockerfile using `_generate_python_dockerfile`\n- **AND** the Dockerfile SHALL include Python base image, dependency installation, entrypoint, and port exposure\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-003-B — Generate Java Dockerfile\n\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL generate a Dockerfile using `_generate_java_dockerfile`\n- **AND** the Dockerfile SHALL include Maven/Java base image, dependency installation, entrypoint, and port exposure\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-003-C — Skip Dockerfile when already exists\n\n- **GIVEN** a `Dockerfile` already exists in the workspace\n- **WHEN** `_generate_dockerfile` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL NOT overwrite the existing Dockerfile\n- **AND** return `None` indicating no new Dockerfile was generated\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-004: Dependency processing\n\nThe system SHALL process agent dependencies based on the language.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-004-A — Process Python dependencies\n\n- **GIVEN** `requirements.txt` exists in a Python workspace\n- **WHEN** `_process_python_dependencies` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL validate the requirements file format\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-004-B — Process Java dependencies\n\n- **GIVEN** `pom.xml` exists in a Java workspace\n- **WHEN** `_process_java_dependencies` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL validate the POM file exists\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-004-C — Missing Python requirements file\n\n- **GIVEN** workspace language is Python but `requirements.txt` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `_process_python_dependencies` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL log a warning but continue (requirements are optional)\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-005: Output preparation\n\nThe system SHALL prepare the output path for the packaged workspace.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-005-A — Default output path\n\n- **GIVEN** `--output` is not specified\n- **WHEN** `_prepare_output_path` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the original workspace path as the output\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-005-B — Custom output path\n\n- **GIVEN** `--output` specifies a custom directory path\n- **WHEN** `_prepare_output_path` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create the output directory if it does not exist\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-005-C — Update metadata after packaging\n\n- **GIVEN** packaging completes successfully\n- **WHEN** `_update_pack_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL save the final `AgentMetadata` to `{output_path}/agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-006: CLI interface\n\nThe system SHALL expose the `pack` command via Typer with specific options.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-006-A — Pack command options\n\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube pack --help`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL display:\n  - `-f, --workspace PATH` — Path to agent workspace (default: \".\")\n  - `--agent-name NAME` — Override agent name\n  - `--language LANG` — Programming language (python, java)\n  - `--entrypoint CMD` — Override entrypoint command\n  - `--port PORT` — Port to expose (default: 8080)\n  - `--build-mode MODE` — Build strategy (local, cloud)\n  - `--description TEXT` — Agent description\n  - `--output PATH` — Output path for packaged workspace\n  - `--verbose` — Enable detailed logging\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-006-B — Successful pack output\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid workspace with all required files\n- **WHEN** `pack` completes without exception\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print success message using Rich `Progress` spinner\n- **AND** display agent name, resolved workspace path, and metadata file path\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-006-C — Pack failure with verbose logging\n\n- **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n- **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is enabled\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red with full traceback\n- **AND** exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-006-D — Pack failure without verbose\n\n- **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n- **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is NOT enabled\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red without traceback\n- **AND** exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-007: Language compatibility validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate that the specified language and port are valid.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-007-A — Valid language specification\n\n- **GIVEN** `--language` is provided as `\"python\"` or `\"java\"` (case-insensitive)\n- **WHEN** `_validate_language_compatibility` runs\n- **THEN** the validation SHALL pass successfully\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-007-B — Invalid language specification\n\n- **GIVEN** `--language` is provided as an unsupported value\n- **WHEN** Pydantic validator runs on the metadata\n- **THEN** validation SHALL fail with `ValueError` indicating valid options are `python` or `java`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-007-C — Port range validation\n\n- **GIVEN** `--port` is provided with a value outside valid range\n- **WHEN** Pydantic validator runs on the metadata\n- **THEN** validation SHALL fail with `ValueError` indicating port must be between 1 and 65535\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-008: Entrypoint inference\n\nThe system SHALL infer the entrypoint command if not explicitly provided.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-008-A — Infer Python entrypoint\n\n- **GIVEN** `--entrypoint` is not provided for a Python agent\n- **WHEN** `_infer_entrypoint` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL look for `main.py` in the workspace root\n- **AND** default to `python main.py` if found\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-008-B — Infer Java entrypoint\n\n- **GIVEN** `--entrypoint` is not provided for a Java agent\n- **WHEN** `_infer_entrypoint` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL look for a main class in `pom.xml`\n- **AND** default to `java -jar target/*.jar` if a JAR is expected\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC001: Pack validates workspace structure before processing\n- [ ] AC002: Pack loads or creates metadata with proper defaults\n- [ ] AC003: Pack merges CLI option overrides into metadata\n- [ ] AC004: Pack generates Dockerfile when needed (Python/Java)\n- [ ] AC005: Pack processes dependencies for the target language\n- [ ] AC006: Pack prepares output path and saves metadata\n- [ ] AC007: Pack displays success output with Rich formatting\n- [ ] AC008: Pack handles errors with proper exit codes and verbose logging\n- [ ] AC009: Pack validates language and port values\n- [ ] AC010: Pack infers entrypoint when not provided\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Notes\n\n### Key Components\n\n| Component | Path | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| CLI Entry | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer app with `pack` command |\n| PackRuntime | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Core packaging logic |\n| MetadataService | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Metadata CRUD operations |\n| AgentMetadata | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Pydantic model for agent config |\n| DockerService | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Dockerfile generation and Docker operations |\n\n### Metadata Fields (AgentMetadata)\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| agent_name | str | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n| language | str | \"python\" | Programming language used |\n| entrypoint | str | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n| port | int | 8080 | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n| build_mode | str | \"local\" | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n| description | Optional[str] | None | Human-readable summary |\n| requirements_file | Optional[str] | \"requirements.txt\" | Python dependency file |\n\n### CLI Options Mapping\n\n| CLI Option | Metadata Field | Type |\n|------------|----------------|------|\n| `--agent-name` | agent_name | Optional[str] |\n| `--language` | language | Optional[str] |\n| `--entrypoint` | entrypoint | Optional[str] |\n| `--port` | port | Optional[int] |\n| `--build-mode` | build_mode | Optional[str] |\n| `--description` | description | Optional[str] |\n| `--output` | (output path) | Optional[str] |\n\n---\n\n# Delta Spec: AR-038 — Go Unit Testing (workloadmanager)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing Go unit tests for the workloadmanager module (`pkg/workloadmanager`).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-038\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: L\n\n## Reference\n\nBase spec: client-go library from `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe workloadmanager module provides workload management for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources in Kubernetes. It includes:\n- WorkloadManager interface for CRUD operations\n- GC (Garbage Collection) worker for expired resource cleanup\n- Expiration checker for TTL and idle timeout\n- Graceful manager for connection draining\n- Cleanup manager for orphaned resources\n- Batch manager for bulk operations\n- HTTP server with REST API endpoints\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Feature: CleanupManager Resource Cleanup\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-001-A — CleanupManager deletes orphaned services\n\n- **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n- **WHEN** cleanupServices is called with a namespace and owner reference\n- **THEN** it should return a list of cleaned service resource strings\n- **AND** services with matching owner references should be deleted\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-001-B — CleanupManager deletes orphaned configmaps\n\n- **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n- **WHEN** cleanupConfigMaps is called with a namespace and owner reference\n- **THEN** it should return a list of cleaned configmap resource strings\n- **AND** configmaps with the annotation `agentcube.volcano.sh/auto-delete=true` and matching owner should be deleted\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-001-C — CleanupManager handles retained PVCs\n\n- **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n- **WHEN** cleanupPVCs is called with a namespace and owner reference for a PVC with Retain policy\n- **THEN** the PVC should not be deleted\n- **AND** other PVCs with matching owner should be deleted\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-001-D — CleanupManager cleans orphaned resources\n\n- **GIVEN** a CleanupManager and a Sandbox object\n- **WHEN** cleanupOrphanedResources is called\n- **THEN** it should clean services, configmaps, and PVCs associated with the sandbox\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-001-E — CleanupManager finds orphaned services\n\n- **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n- **WHEN** FindOrphanedServices is called with namespace and sessionID\n- **THEN** it should return service names that have no owner references\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-001-F — CleanupManager CleanupAllResources\n\n- **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n- **WHEN** CleanupAllResources is called with a sandbox\n- **THEN** it should clean all associated resources\n\n---\n\n### Feature: BatchManager Operations\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-002-A — BatchManager deletes all sandboxes synchronously under threshold\n\n- **GIVEN** a BatchManager with workloadMgr and gracefulMgr\n- **WHEN** handleDeleteAllSandboxes is called with fewer than AsyncThreshold (10) sandboxes\n- **THEN** it should delete all sandboxes synchronously\n- **AND** return a BatchDeleteResponse with deleted and failed counts\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-002-B — BatchManager deletes all sandboxes asynchronously over threshold\n\n- **GIVEN** a BatchManager with workloadMgr and gracefulMgr\n- **WHEN** handleDeleteAllSandboxes is called with more than AsyncThreshold (10) sandboxes\n- **THEN** it should start async deletion in background\n- **AND** return immediately with all items marked as deleted\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-002-C — BatchManager deletes stale sandboxes\n\n- **GIVEN** a BatchManager with workloadMgr and gracefulMgr\n- **WHEN** deleteStaleSandboxes is called\n- **THEN** it should delete all sandboxes in Unknown or Failed state older than StaleStateThreshold (1 hour)\n- **AND** return a BatchDeleteResponse with results\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-002-D — BatchManager deletes by label selector\n\n- **GIVEN** a BatchManager with workloadMgr and gracefulMgr\n- **WHEN** handleDeleteByLabelSelector is called with a label selector\n- **THEN** it should delete all sandboxes matching the label selector\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-002-E — BatchManager public methods\n\n- **GIVEN** a BatchManager\n- **WHEN** DeleteAllInNamespace, DeleteByLabelSelector, or DeleteStaleSandboxes are called\n- **THEN** they should delegate to the appropriate handler methods\n\n---\n\n### Feature: WorkloadManager Sandbox Operations\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-A — GetSandboxBySessionID finds AgentRuntime\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client that has AgentRuntime resources\n- **WHEN** GetSandboxBySessionID is called with a sessionID that exists in an AgentRuntime\n- **THEN** it should return a Sandbox object with correct fields\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-B — GetSandboxBySessionID finds CodeInterpreter\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client that has CodeInterpreter resources\n- **WHEN** GetSandboxBySessionID is called with a sessionID that exists in a CodeInterpreter\n- **THEN** it should return a Sandbox object with correct fields\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-C — GetSandboxBySessionID returns error when not found\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client\n- **WHEN** GetSandboxBySessionID is called with a non-existent sessionID\n- **THEN** it should return ErrSandboxNotFound\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-D — DeleteSandbox deletes AgentRuntime by sessionId\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client that has AgentRuntime with matching sessionId label\n- **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called with namespace, sessionID, and delete options\n- **THEN** it should delete the matching AgentRuntime\n- **AND** return nil on success\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-E — DeleteSandbox deletes CodeInterpreter by sessionId\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client that has CodeInterpreter with matching sessionId label\n- **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called with namespace, sessionID, and delete options\n- **THEN** it should delete the matching CodeInterpreter\n- **AND** return nil on success\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-F — DeleteSandbox applies force delete\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client\n- **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called with Force=true\n- **THEN** it should set GracePeriodSeconds to 0\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-G — DeleteSandbox applies label selector\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client\n- **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called with LabelSelector\n- **THEN** it should use the label selector when listing resources\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-H — ListSandboxes returns combined list\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client that has both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n- **WHEN** ListSandboxes is called with namespace and ListOptions\n- **THEN** it should return a SandboxList containing both types\n- **AND** apply label and field selectors correctly\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Server HTTP Handlers\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-004-A — Server health check endpoint\n\n- **GIVEN** a Server instance\n- **WHEN** GET /healthz is requested\n- **THEN** it should return HTTP 200 with \"ok\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-004-B — Server readiness check - ready\n\n- **GIVEN** a Server with ready=true\n- **WHEN** GET /readyz is requested\n- **THEN** it should return HTTP 200 with status \"ok\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-004-C — Server readiness check - not ready\n\n- **GIVEN** a Server with ready=false\n- **WHEN** GET /readyz is requested\n- **THEN** it should return HTTP 503 with status \"not ready\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-004-D — Server starts and stops cleanly\n\n- **GIVEN** a Server with valid config\n- **WHEN** Start() is called\n- **THEN** it should bind to the configured port\n- **AND** Start() should return nil\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-004-E — Server handles API error mapping\n\n- **GIVEN** a Server with a WorkloadManager that returns an error\n- **WHEN** handleError is called with k8s IsNotFound error\n- **THEN** it should return HTTP 404 with reason \"NotFound\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-004-F — Server corsMiddleware sets headers\n\n- **GIVEN** a Server\n- **WHEN** corsMiddleware processes a request\n- **THEN** it should set Access-Control-Allow-* headers\n- **AND** handle OPTIONS preflight requests\n\n---\n\n### Feature: GracefulManager Operations\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-A — GracefulManager registers connection\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager\n- **WHEN** RegisterConnection is called with a sandboxID\n- **THEN** the active connection count should increment\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-B — GracefulManager unregisters connection\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager with an active connection\n- **WHEN** UnregisterConnection is called with the sandboxID\n- **THEN** the active connection count should decrement\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-C — GracefulManager drains connections\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager\n- **WHEN** drainConnections is called with a sandboxID\n- **THEN** the draining flag should be set to true\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-D — GracefulManager checks if draining\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager with a sandbox marked for draining\n- **WHEN** IsDraining is called with the sandboxID\n- **THEN** it should return true\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-E — GracefulManager gets active connections\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager with registered connections\n- **WHEN** GetActiveConnections is called\n- **THEN** it should return the correct count\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-F — GracefulManager cleans up sandbox state\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager with a sandbox\n- **WHEN** Cleanup is called with the sandboxID\n- **THEN** the sandbox entry should be removed from connections map\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-G — GracefulManager waitForConnections timeout\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager with active connections that never drain\n- **WHEN** waitForConnections is called with a short timeout\n- **THEN** it should return an error after timeout\n\n---\n\n### Feature: K8sClient Initialization\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-006-A — K8sClient NewK8sClient with kubeconfig path\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid kubeconfig path\n- **WHEN** NewK8sClient is called with the path\n- **THEN** it should return a K8sClient with Clientset, KubernetesClient, and DynamicClient\n- **AND** return nil error\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-006-B — K8sClient NewK8sClient with in-cluster mode\n\n- **GIVEN** InClusterMode constant\n- **WHEN** NewK8sClient is called with InClusterMode\n- **THEN** it should attempt in-cluster config\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-006-C — K8sClient NewInClusterClient\n\n- **GIVEN** running inside a Kubernetes cluster\n- **WHEN** NewInClusterClient is called\n- **THEN** it should create clients using in-cluster config\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-006-D — K8sClient expandKubeconfigPath handles tilde\n\n- **GIVEN** a path starting with ~\n- **WHEN** expandKubeconfigPath is called\n- **THEN** it should replace ~ with the home directory\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-006-E — K8sClient expandKubeconfigPath handles empty path\n\n- **GIVEN** an empty string\n- **WHEN** expandKubeconfigPath is called\n- **THEN** it should return the empty string\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Type Helper Functions\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-007-A — NewAPIResponse creates correct response\n\n- **GIVEN** data and metadata\n- **WHEN** NewAPIResponse is called\n- **THEN** it should return an APIResponse with Status=\"Success\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-007-B — NewAPIError creates correct error\n\n- **GIVEN** message, reason, and code\n- **WHEN** NewAPIError is called\n- **THEN** it should return an APIError with Status=\"Failure\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-007-C — sandboxFromAgentRuntime maps running state\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with Running condition\n- **WHEN** sandboxFromAgentRuntime is called\n- **THEN** the returned Sandbox should have State=SandboxStateRunning\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-007-D — sandboxFromAgentRuntime maps failed state\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with Failed condition\n- **WHEN** sandboxFromAgentRuntime is called\n- **THEN** the returned Sandbox should have State=SandboxStateFailed\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-007-E — sandboxFromAgentRuntime maps deleting state\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with DeletionTimestamp\n- **WHEN** sandboxFromAgentRuntime is called\n- **THEN** the returned Sandbox should have State=SandboxStateDeleting\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-007-F — sandboxFromCodeInterpreter maps running state\n\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with Ready=true\n- **WHEN** sandboxFromCodeInterpreter is called\n- **THEN** the returned Sandbox should have State=SandboxStateRunning\n\n---\n\n### Feature: ListExpiredSandboxes\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-008-A — ListExpiredSandboxes returns expired AgentRuntimes\n\n- **GIVEN** a client with AgentRuntime resources\n- **WHEN** ListExpiredSandboxes is called\n- **THEN** it should return sandboxes that have expired\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-008-B — ListExpiredSandboxes returns expired CodeInterpreters\n\n- **GIVEN** a client with CodeInterpreter resources\n- **WHEN** ListExpiredSandboxes is called\n- **THEN** it should return sandboxes that have expired\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-008-C — ListExpiredSandboxes handles empty namespace\n\n- **GIVEN** a client with resources in a namespace\n- **WHEN** ListExpiredSandboxes is called with an empty namespace string\n- **THEN** it should list all expired sandboxes\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Retry Logic\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-009-A — Retry with exponential backoff\n\n- **GIVEN** a function that fails initially then succeeds\n- **WHEN** retry logic is applied\n- **THEN** it should retry with increasing delays\n- **AND** ultimately succeed\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-009-B — Retry stops after max attempts\n\n- **GIVEN** a function that always fails\n- **WHEN** retry logic is applied with max attempts\n- **THEN** it should return the last error after exhausting retries\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC001: All CleanupManager methods must have unit tests covering success and error paths\n- [ ] AC002: All BatchManager methods must have tests with mocked WorkloadManager\n- [ ] AC003: WorkloadManager sandbox operations must have tests with fake clients\n- [ ] AC004: Server HTTP handlers must have tests using httptest\n- [ ] AC005: GracefulManager connection tracking must have unit tests\n- [ ] AC006: K8sClient initialization must have tests for different config modes\n- [ ] AC007: Helper functions (NewAPIResponse, NewAPIError, sandboxFrom*) must have tests\n- [ ] AC008: ListExpiredSandboxes must have tests for both resource types\n- [ ] AC009: Retry logic must have unit tests for backoff behavior\n- [ ] AC010: Existing tests in service_test.go, gc_test.go, expiration_test.go remain passing\n\n---\n\n## Test File Status\n\n| Source File | Test File | Status |\n|-------------|-----------|--------|\n| service.go | service_test.go | Complete |\n| gc.go | gc_test.go | Complete |\n| expiration.go | expiration_test.go | Complete |\n| cleanup.go | cleanup_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| server.go | server_test.go | Complete |\n| graceful.go | graceful_test.go | Complete |\n| batch.go | batch_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| client.go | client_test.go | Complete |\n| delete_test.go | N/A | Exists |\n| retry.go | retry_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n# Delta Spec: AR-041 — E2E 集成测试\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing E2E integration tests for the agentcube client-go library.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-041\n- **Module**: `test/e2e`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: L\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe client-go library provides Kubernetes client code for the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group. It includes:\n- Clientset with typed clients for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n- SharedInformerFactory for caching resources\n- Listers for efficient resource access\n- Fake clients for testing purposes\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Feature: Clientset 创建与配置\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-001-A — 创建标准 Clientset\n\n- **GIVEN** 有效的 Kubernetes rest.Config 配置\n- **WHEN** 调用 `NewForConfig(config)` 创建 Clientset\n- **THEN** 返回非 nil 的 Clientset 实例\n- **AND** 可以通过 `RuntimeV1alpha1()` 访问 v1alpha1 API\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-001-B — 使用 httpClient 创建 Clientset\n\n- **GIVEN** 有效的 Kubernetes rest.Config 和自定义 http.Client\n- **WHEN** 调用 `NewForConfigAndClient(config, httpClient)` 创建 Clientset\n- **THEN** 返回的 Clientset 使用自定义的 httpClient\n- **AND** 所有 API 请求通过自定义的 httpClient 发起\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-001-C — 使用 NewForConfigOrDie 创建 Clientset\n\n- **GIVEN** 有效的 Kubernetes rest.Config 配置\n- **WHEN** 调用 `NewForConfigOrDie(config)` 创建 Clientset\n- **AND** 配置无效时 panic，否则返回正常的 Clientset\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-001-D — 使用 REST 接口创建 Clientset\n\n- **GIVEN** 一个 rest.Interface 实例\n- **WHEN** 调用 `New(restClient)` 创建 Clientset\n- **THEN** 返回的 Clientset 使用传入的 REST 客户端\n- **AND** 支持 RuntimeV1alpha1() 访问\n\n---\n\n### Feature: AgentRuntime CRUD 操作\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-002-A — 创建 AgentRuntime 资源\n\n- **GIVEN** 有效的 AgentRuntime 对象和命名空间 \"default\"\n- **WHEN** 调用 `clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Create(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.CreateOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回创建的 AgentRuntime 对象\n- **AND** 其 Name 与输入对象一致\n- **AND** 其 Namespace 为 \"default\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-002-B — 获取 AgentRuntime 资源\n\n- **GIVEN** 已存在的 AgentRuntime 资源 \"test-runtime\" 在命名空间 \"default\" 中\n- **WHEN** 调用 `clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Get(ctx, \"test-runtime\", metav1.GetOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回对应的 AgentRuntime 对象\n- **AND** 其 Name 为 \"test-runtime\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-002-C — 更新 AgentRuntime 资源\n\n- **GIVEN** 已存在的 AgentRuntime 资源 \"test-runtime\"\n- **WHEN** 调用 `Update(ctx, updatedAgentRuntime, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回更新后的 AgentRuntime 对象\n- **AND** 更新内容已持久化\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-002-D — 更新 AgentRuntime 状态\n\n- **GIVEN** 已存在的 AgentRuntime 资源\n- **WHEN** 调用 `UpdateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回状态已更新的 AgentRuntime 对象\n- **AND** Status 字段已修改\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-002-E — 删除 AgentRuntime 资源\n\n- **GIVEN** 已存在的 AgentRuntime 资源 \"test-runtime\"\n- **WHEN** 调用 `Delete(ctx, \"test-runtime\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回 nil 错误\n- **AND** 资源已被删除\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-002-F — 批量删除 AgentRuntime 资源\n\n- **GIVEN** 多个 AgentRuntime 资源在命名空间中\n- **WHEN** 调用 `DeleteCollection(ctx, deleteOptions, listOptions)`\n- **THEN** 返回 nil 错误\n- **AND** 所有匹配的资源已被删除\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-002-G — 列出所有 AgentRuntime 资源\n\n- **GIVEN** 多个 AgentRuntime 资源存在于集群中\n- **WHEN** 调用 `List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回 AgentRuntimeList 包含所有资源\n- **AND** Items 数组包含所有 AgentRuntime 对象\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-002-H — Watch AgentRuntime 资源变化\n\n- **GIVEN** 有效的 ListOptions 配置\n- **WHEN** 调用 `Watch(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回 watch.Interface\n- **AND** 可以接收资源变更事件\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-002-I — Patch AgentRuntime 资源\n\n- **GIVEN** 已存在的 AgentRuntime 资源和 patch 数据\n- **WHEN** 调用 `Patch(ctx, \"test-runtime\", patchType, data, metav1.PatchOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回 patch 后的 AgentRuntime 对象\n\n---\n\n### Feature: CodeInterpreter CRUD 操作\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-003-A — 创建 CodeInterpreter 资源\n\n- **GIVEN** 有效的 CodeInterpreter 对象和命名空间 \"default\"\n- **WHEN** 调用 `clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(\"default\").Create(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.CreateOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回创建的 CodeInterpreter 对象\n- **AND** 其 Name 与输入对象一致\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-003-B — 获取 CodeInterpreter 资源\n\n- **GIVEN** 已存在的 CodeInterpreter 资源 \"test-interpreter\"\n- **WHEN** 调用 `clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(\"default\").Get(ctx, \"test-interpreter\", metav1.GetOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回对应的 CodeInterpreter 对象\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-003-C — 更新 CodeInterpreter 资源\n\n- **GIVEN** 已存在的 CodeInterpreter 资源\n- **WHEN** 调用 `Update(ctx, updatedCodeInterpreter, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回更新后的 CodeInterpreter 对象\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-003-D — 删除 CodeInterpreter 资源\n\n- **GIVEN** 已存在的 CodeInterpreter 资源\n- **WHEN** 调用 `Delete(ctx, \"test-interpreter\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回 nil 错误\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-003-E — 列出所有 CodeInterpreter 资源\n\n- **GIVEN** 多个 CodeInterpreter 资源存在\n- **WHEN** 调用 `List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回 CodeInterpreterList 包含所有资源\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Informer Factory 使用\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-004-A — 创建 SharedInformerFactory\n\n- **GIVEN** 一个有效的 versioned.Clientset\n- **WHEN** 调用 `NewSharedInformerFactory(clientset, 30*time.Second)`\n- **THEN** 返回 SharedInformerFactory 实例\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-004-B — 启动 Informer\n\n- **GIVEN** 已创建的 SharedInformerFactory\n- **WHEN** 调用 `factory.Start(stopCh)`\n- **THEN** 所有已注册的 informer 开始同步\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-004-C — 等待缓存同步\n\n- **GIVEN** 正在运行的 Informer Factory\n- **WHEN** 调用 `factory.WaitForCacheSync(stopCh)`\n- **THEN** 返回 map[reflect.Type]bool 表示各资源类型的同步状态\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-004-D — 获取 AgentRuntime Informer\n\n- **GIVEN** 已启动的 SharedInformerFactory\n- **WHEN** 调用 `factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes()`\n- **THEN** 返回 AgentRuntimeInformer\n- **AND** 可以获取 Informer 和 Lister\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-004-E — 获取 CodeInterpreter Informer\n\n- **GIVEN** 已启动的 SharedInformerFactory\n- **WHEN** 调用 `factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters()`\n- **THEN** 返回 CodeInterpreterInformer\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-004-F — 使用自定义 resync 间隔\n\n- **GIVEN** versioned.Clientset\n- **WHEN** 调用 `NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client, 60*time.Second, WithCustomResyncConfig(...))`\n- **THEN** Informer 使用自定义的 resync 间隔\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-004-G — 使用 namespace 过滤\n\n- **GIVEN** 需要只监听特定命名空间\n- **WHEN** 使用 `WithNamespace(\"default\")` 选项\n- **THEN** Informer 只监听指定命名空间的资源\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-004-H — 使用 TweakListOptions 自定义 list 请求\n\n- **GIVEN** 需要自定义 list 查询参数\n- **WHEN** 使用 `WithTweakListOptions(func(*metav1.ListOptions))` 选项\n- **THEN** list 请求使用自定义的 ListOptions\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Lister 使用\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-005-A — 列出所有 AgentRuntime\n\n- **GIVEN** 已同步的 AgentRuntime Informer\n- **WHEN** 调用 `lister.List(labels.Everything())`\n- **THEN** 返回所有缓存的 AgentRuntime 对象\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-005-B — 按标签选择 AgentRuntime\n\n- **GIVEN** 已同步的 AgentRuntime 缓存\n- **WHEN** 调用 `lister.List(labels.SelectorFromSet(labels.Set{\"app\": \"test\"}))`\n- **THEN** 返回匹配标签的 AgentRuntime 对象\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-005-C — 获取指定命名空间的 AgentRuntime\n\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeLister 实例\n- **WHEN** 调用 `lister.AgentRuntimes(\"default\")`\n- **THEN** 返回 AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-005-D — 获取指定命名空间中的特定 AgentRuntime\n\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n- **WHEN** 调用 `nsLister.Get(\"test-runtime\")`\n- **THEN** 返回名称为 \"test-runtime\" 的 AgentRuntime 对象\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-005-E — CodeInterpreter Lister 使用\n\n- **GIVEN** 已同步的 CodeInterpreter 缓存\n- **WHEN** 调用 `lister.List(labels.Everything())`\n- **THEN** 返回所有缓存的 CodeInterpreter 对象\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Fake Client 使用\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-006-A — 创建 Fake Clientset\n\n- **GIVEN** 无需连接真实集群\n- **WHEN** 调用 `fake.NewSimpleClientset(...)`\n- **THEN** 返回内存中的 fake Clientset\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-006-B — Fake Client 执行 Create 操作\n\n- **GIVEN** Fake Clientset\n- **WHEN** 调用 `fakeClientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Create(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.CreateOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回创建的对象存储在内存中\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-006-C — Fake Client 执行 Get 操作\n\n- **GIVEN** 已通过 Create 存入的 AgentRuntime\n- **WHEN** 通过 fake Clientset 获取\n- **THEN** 返回之前存储的对象\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-006-D — Fake Client 执行 List 操作\n\n- **GIVEN** 多个已存储的 AgentRuntime\n- **WHEN** 通过 fake Clientset 列出\n- **THEN** 返回所有已存储的对象\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-006-E — Fake Client 执行 Watch 操作\n\n- **GIVEN** Fake Clientset 和 watch 客户端\n- **WHEN** 调用 `Watch(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`\n- **THEN** 返回可以接收事件的 watch.Interface\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-006-F — Fake Scheme 注册\n\n- **GIVEN** Fake Clientset\n- **WHEN** 执行资源操作\n- **THEN** 自动使用注册的 Scheme 进行序列化\n\n---\n\n### Feature: 完整 E2E 流程测试\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-007-A — 完整的 AgentRuntime 生命周期\n\n- **GIVEN** 运行的 Kubernetes 集群和有效配置\n- **WHEN** 按顺序执行: Create → Get → Update → UpdateStatus → Delete\n- **THEN** 完整生命周期正确执行\n- **AND** 每步操作返回正确的对象和状态\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-007-B — 使用 Informer 和 Lister 进行资源监听\n\n- **GIVEN** 运行的集群和 Clientset\n- **WHEN** 创建 SharedInformerFactory → 启动 → 等待同步 → 使用 Lister 查询\n- **THEN** Lister 返回的缓存数据与直接 API 查询一致\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-007-C — 并发资源操作\n\n- **GIVEN** 多个并发创建的请求\n- **WHEN** 同时创建多个 AgentRuntime 资源\n- **THEN** 所有资源正确创建\n- **AND** 最终列表包含所有资源\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-007-D — 错误处理 - 资源不存在\n\n- **GIVEN** 不存在的资源名称\n- **WHEN** 调用 Get 操作\n- **THEN** 返回 `errors.IsNotFound(err)` 为 true\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-007-E — 错误处理 - 权限不足\n\n- **GIVEN** 没有创建权限的配置\n- **WHEN** 尝试创建资源\n- **THEN** 返回包含 \"forbidden\" 或类似信息的错误\n\n---\n\n### Feature: 集成场景测试\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-008-A — AgentRuntime 与 CodeInterpreter 关联\n\n- **GIVEN** 需要创建关联的资源\n- **WHEN** 先创建 AgentRuntime，再创建引用它的 CodeInterpreter\n- **THEN** CodeInterpreter 能正确引用 AgentRuntime\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-008-B — 批量操作性能测试\n\n- **GIVEN** 大批量资源\n- **WHEN** 创建 1000 个 AgentRuntime 资源\n- **THEN** 所有资源创建成功\n- **AND** List 操作在合理时间内返回\n\n#### Scenario: AR-041-008-C — Informer 事件处理\n\n- **GIVEN** 运行中的 Informer 和资源变化\n- **WHEN** 外部创建/更新/删除资源\n- **THEN** Informer 事件被正确触发\n- **AND** Lister 缓存同步更新\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC001: Clientset 创建测试通过 (NewForConfig, NewForConfigAndClient, NewForConfigOrDie, New)\n- [ ] AC002: AgentRuntime CRUD 操作测试通过 (Create, Get, Update, UpdateStatus, Delete, DeleteCollection, List, Watch, Patch)\n- [ ] AC003: CodeInterpreter CRUD 操作测试通过\n- [ ] AC004: SharedInformerFactory 测试通过 (创建, 启动, 等待同步, 获取 informer)\n- [ ] AC005: AgentRuntime 和 CodeInterpreter Informer 测试通过\n- [ ] AC006: Informer Factory 选项测试通过 (WithCustomResyncConfig, WithNamespace, WithTweakListOptions)\n- [ ] AC007: Lister 测试通过 (List, Get, namespace lister)\n- [ ] AC008: Fake Client 测试通过 (Create, Get, List, Watch)\n- [ ] AC009: 完整生命周期测试通过\n- [ ] AC010: 错误处理测试通过 (NotFound, Forbidden)\n\n---\n\n## Test File Status\n\n| Source File | Test File | Status |\n|-------------|-----------|--------|\n| clientset.go | clientset_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n| runtime_client.go | runtime_client_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n| agentruntime.go | agentruntime_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n| codeinterpreter.go | codeinterpreter_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n| factory.go | factory_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n| agentruntime.go (informer) | agentruntime_informer_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n| codeinterpreter.go (informer) | codeinterpreter_informer_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n| agentruntime.go (lister) | agentruntime_lister_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n| codeinterpreter.go (lister) | codeinterpreter_lister_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n| fake/clientset.go | fake_clientset_test.go | **Needs Implementation** |\n\n---\n\n## Testing Patterns\n\n### Test Environment Setup\n- Use envtest (kubebuilder) for integration tests\n- Create temporary Kubernetes API server for testing\n- Use fake clients for unit tests\n\n### E2E Test Structure\n```go\nfunc TestAgentRuntimeE2E(t *testing.T) {\n    // Setup: Start test environment\n    // Given: Create test resources\n    // When: Perform operations\n    // Then: Verify results\n}\n```\n\n### Test File Naming\n- Follow Go convention: `*_test.go`\n- E2E tests in `test/e2e/` package\n- Use `testify` for assertions\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Client-go library: `client-go/`\n- API Group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh / v1alpha1`\n- Resources: AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter\n- Source reference: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`","additions":408,"deletions":2},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775884786715,"end":1775884786769}}}}
